Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_180_Battle_Point_Booster_:
Use this item to increase the rate at which you earn Battle Points to 180% for 500 game minutes. Additionally, you will grant other players a stacking 16% bonus to their Battle Points rate.

Battle Point Boosters are only consumed whenever Battle Points are earned and features like spectating games or coaching do not deplete them.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bonehunter_Spineguard: The Bonehunters believe that if it is good enough to protect from within, then it must also be good enough to protect from without.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bonehunter_Tuskguard: It is tradition that a Bonehunter adorns himself with the teeth of their fiercest kill.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bones_of_the_Slain_Dragon: Includes all of the items in the 'Bones of the Slain Dragon' set for Dragon Knight:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Boneslayer: When Ostarion came to conquer, this blade was presented as a gift in hope of negotiating a peaceful surrender.  It didn't work.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bonkers_the_Mad: From the treetops, Bonkers watched. He saw the sick and infirm tended to, the malicious cursed, the rituals, the rites, the traditions of a Witch Doctor. Bonkers brought this wild knowledge to his kin, and for doing so was banished, called mad in his tongue. Perhaps he is, but now he knows his true calling.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bonus_Gift: A gift for being awesome! Open it up to receive a prize.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_BoraDota: 32 teams in Brazil compete for R$600 in this World Cup style format tournament!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_BoraDota_2nd_Edition: The BoraDota 2nd edition Brazilian Cup consists of 64 teams divided into 16 groups competing for a R$2,000 prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_BoraDota_Stars: The best teams in South America compete in the BoraDota Stars for a prize pool of R$1,500!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Boredgamercouk_Dota2_One_: One Day EU West Dota 2 Tournament
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bottom_Watcher: From far below, a dweller of the deeps has been pressed into service at the surface!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bounty_Hunter_Series: The Dota 2 King of the Hill Bounty Hunter Series returns! Two invited teams teams to go head-to-head for a chance to win $1000. Bundle includes Raiq courier!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bounty_Hunter_Series_Tick: The Dota 2 King of the Hill Bounty Hunter Series returns! Two invited teams teams to go head-to-head for a chance to win $1000. This ticket only gives you access to view games in the Bounty Hunter Series.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_Forsaken_Beauty: Twin snakes coil around a bow of wood and stone.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Crypt_Guardian: A jagged bow for a burning soul.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Crystal_Caves: Beneath her secret glades, Drow found a passage lit by crystal shards. Following the glittering light to the farthest cavern, she discovered this bow, embedded in the rock as if it had formed there.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Eldwurms_Touch: Includes ability icons and ambient particles.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Frostfangs: A great bow of unknown origins, it was wielded by a snow demon that came to challenge the Drow Ranger. The Demon's skill was found wanting and so Traxex found a new weapon for herself.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Moon_Rider: The power of the lunar lioness purrs  in this bow's enchanted string.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Oyoloe: Once thought to be a mythical beast, the Windranger slew the elusive, green oyoloe, and made a bow from its antlers.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Searing_Soul: A bow brought back from hell itself.   With this weapon, enemies will feel the searing burn of your anger.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Serpent: A grove of ancient and magical trees rises from the tangled heart of the Yama Raskav Jungle, and in its gnarled roots and branches may be found a unique and singularly deadly species of viper. The tribes of Yama Raskav tell of a bow crafted from the wood of this grove, infused with the crystallized venom of the serpents which dwell there. In MedusaÃ¢ÂÂs vengeful hands, the Bow of the Serpent is as swift and deadly as the bite of the viper for which it is named.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Shadowcat: A bow made of skin, fur, ebony and finest pieces of drow metal.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Sun_Vine: This beautiful bow, modeled after the delicate and poisonous sun vine, is even more deadly than its namesake.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracer_and_Band: Rare is the ogre that can recall their lineage and lucky is the one with claim to an inheritance.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracer_of_Sir_Davion: Achieving mastery against dragons is impossible without first achieving mastery of the self.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracer_of_the_Burning_Cab: Manipulation of the fire elements requires a delicate touch, lest the sorcerer burn. This pair of bracers have been imbued with minor fire protection enchantments.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracer_of_the_Mage_Slayer: These bracers are made to defend against both swords and sorcery.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracer_of_the_Purist_Cham: Omniknight wears his feelings on his sleeve.  That and a red bracer, which he'll use to smite his enemies in the name of the Omniscience.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracer_of_the_Tahlin_Watc: As he fled his family's slaughter, Riki disguised himself with the armor of his royal watch in order to escape undetected.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_Sleek: The mighty centaur needs no shield when protected by these durable bracers of Omexe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Claszureme: The spikes on the wrist are said to sample the flow of time, while the runes report the findings to the wearer.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Eldritch_Ice: The charmed ropes that once bound him should have rotted away, but Lich has preserved them as reminder to all that no power in creation can hope to hold him.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Forsaken_Beaut: Rubies stud these bracers. Medusa now mocks the beauty which she once held dear.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Fury: These arm  guards protect against the occasional wayward strike of your own flail.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Impending_Tran: The better to kill and cauterize.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Profound_Perfe: While many wizards are jealous of the Invoker's unimaginable power, others are merely jealous of his peerless taste.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Shifting_Forms: In battle, these bracers, ever before Morphling's gaze, remind him of the power of Polymorphia.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_The_Howling_Wo: Bone-carved arm bracers display the ceremonial markings of the Frosted Winds tribe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Yoskreth: As the Anti-Mage grew in power and prestige, the sovereign of Yoskreth sought his services to topple the fearsome sorcerer Sahsk.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Archivist: For turning pages that wish not to be turned, the Archivist's bracers have been imbued with persuasive powers.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Awakened: May thine Hatred lend thee the strength to shatter the symbol of thine bretheren's demise, for within its remains lies absolute power! - Taken from Tael'Am
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Clergy_Asc: A constant reminder of the world he left behind when he struck off on the ascetic's path.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Crystallin: Hard as ice, but strong as steel, these bracers bring a chill to the heart of those who would oppose the maiden of the north.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Dark_Magic: Those who practiced the magical arts are often feared for their power.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Death_Char:
With these bracers, the Spirit Breaker is prepared for any brouhaha.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Drake: Made from the scales of a drake's underbelly, this light and colorful armor is an honor to wear into battle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Ebony_Towe: A lord so adorned will bend the will of many.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Frozen_Fea: A day before the wizard descended into the glacier to begin his hibernation, he offered Crystal Maiden these last, precious gifts: armor and a staff, strong as ice but light as a feather, believed to have once belonged to a winter deity.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Gwimyeon_W: One must never neglect the protection of one's swordhand.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Hidden_Tal: These bracers bespeak a man who will brook no magical manipulations!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Hierophant: A Hierophant of the Omniscience must always guard against any threat.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Malicious_: Of flowing dark and unknown aethers come arms of dangerous beauty.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Moon_Rider: The moon shines with mystic lustre on Mirana's forearms...or is it the glow of these polished bracers?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Radiant_Cr: They are as pristine as the day they were made, but do not be fooled into thinking they have never seen combat.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Revenant: A new storm is blowing across the battlefield.  Where there is thunder, there is sure to be lighting.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Seasoned_H: Rule number one, always come prepared!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Shifting_S:
The eccentric sorcerer Throsho required unique armaments able to conform to his shapeshifting form.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Silent_Gua: These powerful bracers protect their wearer from the ravages battle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Braces_of_the_Atniw: A projection of will.  A show of might.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Braided_Tail_of_the_Conqu: A braid woven into the tail of a centaur signifies that battle is soon at hand.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bramblehorn: She who rides a tiger is afraid to dismount.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Brawler_of_the_Glacier_Se: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Brawler of the Glacier Sea' set for Tusk plus a loading screen and ability icons.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Braze_the_Zonkey: Separated from his herd when disruptions to the traditional migratory route took it through a tesseract, he stands out a bit in this new habitat. But that's all right. Apart from enemy heroes, he has no natural predators!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Brazilian_Dota_League: 20 teams will compete in the first season of the Brazilian Dota League for a total prize pool of R$350!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Breastplate_of_the_Slithe: As strong as it is beautifully crafted, this breastplace armor provides protection against the hazards of the deep.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bridon_League_Open_Cup: 4 teams from qualification will compete with guest stars for a prize of 500,000 RUB
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Broken_Shackles: It is unwise, and often quite fatal, to underestimate an ogre's strength!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Brooch_of_Deaths_Bride: No stories remain of the woman who taught Krobelus her skill, only heirlooms and rumor.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Brooch_of_the_Gleaming_Se:
Above a pallid brow do death's feathers roost.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Brooch_of_the_Third_Insig: There is little a mind cannot assess provided it is properly equipped.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Brood_Hunter_Bundle: This bundle contains the Brood Hunter Hud Skin and Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Brunei_Dota_League_2014: The first season of the Brunei Dota League gives amateur teams an opportunity to compete and improve their game play!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Brutal_Crescent_of_the_Co: With this silver crescent, the centaur has cut the strings of many lives.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Buckler_of_the_Bramble_Lo: The grim visage of the Bramble Lord adorns the deflector.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bucktooth_Jerry: A fan of the forest, Jerry fashioned wings and horns from the wood of a sacred Windwood tree. But don't believe the rumors that he made his famous teeth out of the same stuff. They're real. Just ask any nut he's bitten.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bulgarian_Amateur_League_: This is the third season for the Bulgarian Amateur League. It's an open league with up to 50 teams competing for a prize.
A Bulgarian League with 50 teams which will compete for 23 days for a prize!
This is the second season for the Bulgarian Amateur League. It's an open league with up to 50 teams competing for a prize.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Burden_of_the_Exiled_Roni: Upon Juggernaut's exile, a mask was bestowed upon his neck that would impart he was indeed a Ronin without a master.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Burden_of_the_Highborn: To restore his family's rule, and to govern those of his kingdom; these are the burdens Riki strives toward.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Burning_Iron: Belching fire and death, he screams across burning skies. Can't stop the rider!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Burning_Spear: A spear of sharpened rock blades imbued with magical fire.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Burning_scepter_of_the_An: Includes custom ability icons when equiped.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Butch: There’s only a handful of beasts that could appreciate a good slab of meat more than a butcher.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Butter_Blunder: As busy as they are clumsy, butter blunders are known for their butterfingers.  What they lack in dexterity, they make up for in their earnest desire to please.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Buttercup: The dead of battle can breed many an odd fungus.  That suits Buttercup just fine.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Buttercups_Barding: It is a strange thing that such a calm and gentle creature as Buttercup be made to seem so fierce.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Butterfly_Cup_Ve_Dota2: Ve_Dota2 community presents the Butterfly Cup! Sixteen Latin American teams will fight for more than $300 in prizes and glory.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Button_Down_of_the_Voyage: A dozen brass buttons, and triple-stitched by a master sailmaker, it would take an unusually determined prospective mate to surmount this formidable fortress of...chastity?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_BuzzCraft_Dota_2_League_#: Semiprofessional teams will compete with each other in the Dota 2  arena  fora prize of 30,000 rubles.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CCC_League: Players from Ukraine will fight for a prize pool of items.

Teams compete in a 8 week regular season followed by a double-elimination playoff bracket where they compete for cash prizes and a chance to advance to higher skill divisions in future seasons.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CEVO_Season_4: CEVO Season 4 is a North American Pro-Am event where teams compete in an 8-week regular season, followed by playoffs for over $5,000 and the chance to advance to higher skill divisions in future seasons.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CEVO_Season_5: CEVO Season 5 is a North American Pro-Am event where teams compete in an 8-week regular season, followed by Playoffs for over $1,000 and the chance to advance to higher skill divisions in future seasons. This ticket only gives you access to view games from CEVO Season 5.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CIS_Carnage_2014: CIS Carnage 2014 features 8 well-known CIS teams competing for a total prize pool of $4,000. This ticket only gives you access to view games from CIS Carnage 2014.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CIS_Carnage_2014_Bundle: CIS Carnage 2014 features 8 well-known CIS teams competing for a total prize pool of $4,000. Includes Grievous Ingots for Invoker!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CIS_Dota_2_Leage_Season_2: 16 semi-pro teams compete for a $200 prize pool. This bundle gives access to view games from the CIS Dota 2 League Season 2 and the Force of Spirit HUD.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CIS_Dota_2_League: 32 teams compete in the CIS Dota 2 League for a grand prize of $200!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CIS_Dota_2_League_Season_: 16 semi-pro teams compete for a $200 prize pool. This ticket only gives access to view games from the CIS Dota 2 League Season 2.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CI_Cyber_League_Second_Cu: 32 amateur teams compete for the grand prize.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CLG_Pennant: Show your support for a team by buying this Team Pennant! Equip it in the 'fan slot' of your Player Loadout to show other spectators who you're rooting for. Upgrade it to show you mean business! In addition, equipping a pennant makes you eligible for item drops while you spectate your team's matches live during Valve supported tournaments.  Pennants can be combined with other pennants to upgrade your Team Pennant fan level.  The level of your Team Pennant will increase the total fan value of the team when you are spectating a Tournament match.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CSPLRU_Dota_2_League_Seas: The second season of the lasting battle, where more than 500 players will compete for the prize and the championship title!
The third season long battle where over 500 participants compete for prizes and the right to call themselves the champions.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CSPL_Dota_2_League_Season: The first season of continuous battle where more than 500 different players will fight for a prize and the title of champion!
The second season of the CSPL Dota 2 League continues where more than a thousand different players will fight for a prize and the title of champion!

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cadenza_Magic_Master: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Cadenza Magic Master' set for Invoker plus loading screen and custom forge spirit. These items were created in partnership with LGD-Gaming, who receive a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Call_of_the_Dendrochron: This item changes the appearance of the treant warriors summoned by Nature's Call. Even the dreaded axe cannot hold their kind in check.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cannonade:
Within an admiral's hand Cannonade shines brightly, pointing the way for the blast to come.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cap_of_the_Fungal_Lord: Infused with the essence of the Father Mushroom.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_Arcane_Artistry: An archmagister must be the greatest at all things magical: spell-casting, scroll-reading, and costume-wearing.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_Thunderwraths_Cal: Only those who are called in service to the Omniscient can wear a cape such as this.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_Verdant_Dreaming: Wrapped in the power of the ancient woods.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Burning_Cabal: The invokers of the Burning Cabal favor Exort over all other disciplines.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Crystalline_Q: Nights are cold in the contested lands, but for some, not cold enough.  This frost-charmed cape keeps cold what the sun would warm.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Dark_Magic: To the Invoker, those without the gifts of magic are insects to be ignored or destroyed.  For at time, his ferocity was such that the magical arts were treated with superstition and fear by all.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Drake: A long cape designed in honor of all drakes who have died in battle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Flameguard: The Flameguard wear capes as blue as the Holy Flame they are sworn to protect. On the back is their sigil: a circle representing the Inner Colannade with an inscribed triangle symbolizing the Flame itself.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Frozen_Feathe: A day before the wizard descended into the glacier to begin his hibernation, he offered Crystal Maiden these last, precious gifts: armor and a staff, strong as ice but light as a feather, believed to have once belonged to a winter deity.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Glacier_Duste:
A well-woven cape of dyed wolf pelt.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Gleaming_Seal:
A sweep of movement, a shift of dark leather, are all that the dead will have time to see.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Great_Safari: Simple, elegant, ripped from a corpse.  The scap of banner taken from a Vigil Knight now makes a fine cape for a Keen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Wind_Leaf: A cape for all weather, this is a garment that any falconer would be proud to wear.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Captain_Bamboo: Not just a Panda, He's a Captain!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Captains_Hook: In waters as treacherous as those that surround the Trembling Isle, it is inevitable that even the most skilled captain sustain injury.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Carapace_of_Bukivak_the_C: Far away beneath the Sunken Cities and through the Infernal Hollow, Buki'vak the Corrupted dwells in the depths forever expanding his corruption throughout the sea. Hearing of his power, Lion seeked to harvest his parts for a fresh demonoplasty. After a strenuous battle he defeated Buki'vak and gained the hand he desired as a reward, but it was not without cost. Just as his previous hand transformed him, so did this one. He became afflicted with the Malignant Corruption, causing unseemly shards of Obsidian to grow from his body and further disfigure him into something even more unrecognizeable from his original form.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Carapace_of_the_Chosen_La: Molted over the course of seven seasons by the slow administration of special alchemicals, this carapace is hardened against both blade and spell.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Carapace_of_the_Hidden_Hi: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Carapace of the Hidden Hive' set for Nyx Assassin:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Carved_Grin_of_the_Tricks: But does Yurnero ever smile beneath the mask?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Castors_Spaulder: The riverlands hero Castor Twin-Tusks challenged Verodicia's chosen prophet to an arcane duel. He lost.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Catalyst_Cap: The perfect accoutrement for when Lina wishes to Mix things up a bit. Which is almost always.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cauldron_of_Xahryx: Until at Sylla's paw the vile Xahryx fell asunder, the wildest power known was held within the cauldron's depths. In fear of what evil may seek such strength was the vessel taken, and put to heroic purpose.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Caustic_Steel_Set: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Caustic Steel' set for Alchemist:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cavalier_of_Anarchy: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Cavalier of Anarchy' set for Chaos Knight plus a loading screen:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Celestial_Observatory: This ancient ward has stood watch nearly as long as the stars themselves.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cercus_of_Whirling_Death: Sandking uses these pincers as another set of hands, grappling onto prey as they scuttle above his sandy hideaway.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cerebral_Support: What ancient beast once wore this?  The Tidehunter cares not.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ceremonial_Carapace_of_Qa: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Ceremonial Carapace of Qaldin' set for Sand King:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ceremonial_Claws_of_Qaldi: Incised with the luminous runes of Qezh, the upraised claws of the Scintillant Supplicant summon the full attention of the Djinn of Qaldin.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ceremonial_Crawlers_of_Qa: All the rites of Qaldin are done as dance, with each step prescribed and enacted in precise detail. A misstep can mean an age of misfortune. But Sand King has never put one crawler wrong.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ceremonial_Horns: The avatar of Nature's Wrath may take whatever form he pleases. Choosing sometimes to appear as tree, other times as predator, or when it suits him as prey.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ceremonial_Pshent_of_Qald: The sentient sands of the Scintillant Waste don this glorious headpiece for only their most sacred rites.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ceremonial_Rapier: More a prize than a weapon, this rapier was looted from some unfortunate prince's treasure ship as it navigated the Narrow Channel.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ceremonial_Stinger_of_Qal: At the height of the ceremony of Qaz'hallaq, seven virtuous acolytes are stung to death with one swipe of this malevolent armored appendage.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ceremonial_Thorax_of_Qald: Behold! This ritual adornment celebrates the flawless power of the Djinn who first poured the Sentient Sand into a suit of magical armor. Flawless and mighty, like the Djinn itself, a thorax for only the most sacred of occasions.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chain_of_Enduring_Torment: She may be chained, but she is still in control.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chained_Chopper: Tangled in the links of Pudge's chains, a reminder of the shackles that bind us to life--and how easily Pudge may break them.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chained_Guard: A little armor can go a long way.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chained_Snatcher: Never give a meal the chance to be late for dinner.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chained_Spur: Delight in pain as they squeal with agony.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chained_Wings: Let her have you, and she will keep you.

Any resulting items are subject to the same trade restrictions as the Treasure of the Crafter's Relic.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chronite_Armor: The time-altering properties of chronite stabilizes the Faceless Void's presence in the material realm.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chronite_Bracers: A pair of chronite encrusted bracers that seem to warn the Faceless Void of his enemies' future attacks.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chronite_Scepter: A symbol of power within the infinite halls of Claszureme.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chronoptic_Crown: Heavy is the head that wears this crown.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chuangleague: The Chuangleague is a ShanghaiLanyou Cultural Communications Limited company held tournament. This league is a NewBee club competition for all Chinese College Students.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cinch_of_the_Mortal_Coil: A fine crimson cloth adorned by the Death Prophet.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Circlet_of_Forsaken_Beaut: A circlet of golden laurels holds the delicate veil that hid Medusa's once-beautiful face.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Circlet_of_the_Northern_W: Worn proudly wherever she goes, Lyralei reminds the world that it is her business to turn back the inevitable, and discover victory where others have foretold defeat.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Circlet_of_the_Purist_Cha: For Omniknight, no show of loyalty is too great.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Circuito_LVP_Dota_2: Some of the best teams in Spain compete for the 3,500 Euro prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Cudgel: After many years, Leviathan recently stumbled upon the sunken wreckage of his rival's fleet. He now wields the mast of their flagship as a cudgel, and woe betide any who get in his way.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Gauntlets: The only piece of equipment left on Kunkka after he washed up on a Keen shore.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Guard: A high collar keeps salty waters and harsh weather from marring Kunkka's visage, while heavy shoulder-plates have deflected many a tooth and claw belonging to such abominations as lurk in the murky waters.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Hightops: These steel toe-guards are effective at fending off sea monsters, as well as punishing booties of lazy Keen sailors.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Voyagers_Chestpl: Don't let the plate fool you; he'd much rather the jacket survived the battle unharmed.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Voyagers_Elegant: If you're going to travel, do it in style.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Voyagers_First_C: For when a sword won't do.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Voyagers_Gloves: The quality of an admiral's gloves is directly related to how well they can grip a sword.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Voyagers_Helm: The steel sweep and sprouting brush are said to be of Kunkka's own design.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Voyagers_Second_: For when both a sword and a pistol still won't do.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Voyagers_Treads: When you walk the deck, make sure they know who's in charge.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claive_of_Unyielding_Ston: When Sven stands his ground, this blade stands with him.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Clash_of_Pubs: A league for the causal pubers to show their competitive spirit.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claw_Dota_League__The_Cha: The tournament brings together amateur and semi-professional teams for an amazing contest.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claw_Dota_League__Wekeend: An amateur championship Dota 2 for the South American scene.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claw_of_the_Ancient_Sover: In the fragmentary legends of the Ancient Sovereign, death by such claws was something greatly to be desired.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claw_of_the_Haruspex: Serpent Clan long held to the traditions of the haruspex, and so foresaw the ruin and war that would visit the ancient clans.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claws_of_the_Hidden_Hive: When the new Nyx Assassin is chosen, he is sent to the Hidden Hive for confirmation. These claws connote completion of the Assassin's first assignment.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cleaver_of_the_Hidden_Hun: An already heavy blade, made even heavier by the weighted ring looped through the top. This is not a weapon for finesse, but for taking the enemy's head in a single strike.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cleft_Hawks_Call: One among the many striders of Upland Druud, the timid Cleft Hawk makes its home within the many fissures dotting the plains.  The mating call of a Cleft Hawk is said to be as grating as it is unbelievably loud.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Clergy_Warhammer: When you are Omniknight's hammer, every opponent resembles a nail.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_Inscrutable_Zeal: To have a hope of examining the darkened wilds undetected requires clothing fit for subtlety.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Boreal_Watch: Three layers of cloth and fur help to guard against the northern winds.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Dark_Wraith: Mortred's choice of garb is as mysterious as her choice of target.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Dawn: The Bear Clan taught that every rising sun was a gift, and so appointed one among them to greet the dawn each day.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Demonic_Vess: These items were created in partnership with Alliance, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Haruspex: As Serpent Clan spread word of their coming doom, they granted their honored vestments to Sylla that he may remember their words.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Nimble_Edge: To guard against things unseen and unknown.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Northern_Win: In certain parts of certain worlds, the Northern wind blows warm, with a promise of eternal spring.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Stormcrow: A cloak crafted from the feathers and talons of the stormcrow.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Clockwerk_Announcer_Pack: This pack replaces the Default announcer and Mega-Kills announcer with the metal moxie of Clockwerk. Includes the Telebolt Projektor cog item for Clockwerk!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloth_of_the_Clergy_Ascet: What clergy approved this lurid wrap and thought it suitable for an ascetic lifestyle? None survive to justify their decision.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloud_Forged_Great_Bracer: Solid bracers with a wide surace area designed to block a wide variety of attacks.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloud_Forged_Great_Girdle: Strips of cloth gilded with mithril and fastened to a sturdy girdle. The trail of this belt is spoken of among foot soldiers who gaze to the sky above to see Dragonus fly through the clouds.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloud_Forged_Great_Helm: This ornate helm was once seen worn by royal guards of the nest.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloud_Forged_Great_Mantle: This mantle dons a masterful shape to deflect blades but its deeper enchantments protect from sorcery as well.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloud_Forged_Great_Staff: A shard of cloud crystal inlaid with a strip of skywrath gold there is no finer conductor for sorcery than this great staff.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloud_Forged_Great_Wings: Arcane energy resonates across the raven-like feathers of these magic infused wings.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cluckles_the_Brave: Many critters can be trained to ferry tools into battle.  Few will do so while wearing a jetpack!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Coat_of_the_Elder_Grove: A coat of leaves, common amongst the Druids of Verodicia, worn now by Nature's own prophet.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Coat_of_the_Scarlet_Raven: Fly from this raven or die where you stand. In the end, it's all the same.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Coco_the_Courageous: True courage is not how high you can hold a sword but how high you can hold your spirit... And sometimes, even the strongest of heroes need their spirit boosted! Introducing Coco, a courageous courier of the Redpaw Brewery, determined to bring brew to the battlefield at any cost! No longer shall a heroes thirst go unquenched! The call for brew is sacred and by oath it must be upheld! The brew must flow.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Code62_Open_Cup_Season_2: 16 team compete in this open tournament for an invite to the next Open Cup and to get a part of the 2,000,000+ RP prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cold_Case_Bow: Twin-frost orbs charge this bow with arcane energy.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Coliseum_League: 32 teams compete for the top spot in the first Coliseum League.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Coliseum_League_2: Second edition of the Coliseum League with 32 teams competing for a place in the Dota Coliseum hall of fame.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Collar_of_the_Mage_Slayer: Those whom the Anti-Mage hunts may be as skilled with a sword as they are with a spell, and so this collar was crafted to turn their blades aside.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Colossal_Crystal_Chorus:
I spent years digging in Singer's Gulch, trying to track down one of them resonant crystals to sell at the market. I might have only found one, but what a find! Of course, nobody wants to buy it off me for all the noise it makes...
	
	With Aghanim's Scepter, each Meepo will have its own fixed Pooftone.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Commanders_Cape_of_the_Fl: The Flameguard wear capes as blue as the Holy Flame they are sworn to protect. On the back is their sigil: a circle representing the Inner Colannade with an inscribed triangle symbolizing the Flame itself. This variation is the armor of a Flameguard commander.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Commanders_Gauntlet_of_th: An armored gauntlet of the Flameguard sect, worn by that faction's gloried commanders.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Commanders_Helm_of_the_Fl: The Flameguard sect of the Vigil Knights are sworn to protect the ever-burning Holy Flame. While few in number, they are unmatched in swordsmanship.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Commanders_Skirt_of_the_F: Beyond reproach and unwavering in their devotion, the Flameguard stand as living avatars of Knightly Duty. This variation is the armor of a Flameguard commander.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Commanding_Rod_of_the_Pen: Though it does not have the heft of the traditional rod, it lacks none of its potency.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Compass_Edge_of_the_Voyag: A blade that invisibly orients its victim's soul to true death.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Complexity_Pennant: Show your support for a team by buying this Team Pennant! Equip it in the 'fan slot' of your Player Loadout to show other spectators who you're rooting for. Upgrade it to show you mean business! In addition, equipping a pennant makes you eligible for item drops while you spectate your team's matches live during Valve supported tournaments.  Pennants can be combined with other pennants to upgrade your Team Pennant fan level.  The level of your Team Pennant will increase the total fan value of the team when you are spectating a Tournament match.

Available until January 3rd. Use this item to increase the rate at which you earn Battle Points by 400% for 500 game minutes. Additionally, you will grant other players a stacking 80% bonus to their Battle Points rate.

Battle Point Boosters are only consumed whenever Battle Points are earned and features like spectating games or coaching do not deplete them.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cowl_of_Ice: In the frigid north, that which is lost to myth may still be found within the ice. In an age now lost to time, the Frozen Witch Yulsaria ruled the whitelands, summoning blizzards and hail storms upon those who displeased her, while an army of ice golems roamed the lands to snuff out all warmth. In time, her southward expansion angered the Eldwurm Slyrak who, in his terrible rage, melted Yulsaria's armies with his endless flame before conquering the Frozen Witch herself. Now, centuries later, shifts in the ice have heaved up the last remaining shard of her empire: her glacial crown.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cowl_of_the_Blood_Covenan: He needs not eyes, who is guided by the sight of the Flayed ones.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cowl_of_the_Blood_Stained: The hunter hides his face for various reasons, but in the desert wastes the sun is enemy enough.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cowl_of_the_Boreal_Watch: For those who wish their face never to be seen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cowl_of_the_Malignant_Cor: Far away beneath the Sunken Cities and through the Infernal Hollow, Buki'vak the Corrupted dwells in the depths forever expanding his corruption throughout the sea. Hearing of his power, Lion seeked to harvest his parts for a fresh demonoplasty. After a strenuous battle he defeated Buki'vak and gained the hand he desired as a reward, but it was not without cost. Just as his previous hand transformed him, so did this one. He became afflicted with the Malignant Corruption, causing unseemly shards of Obsidian to grow from his body and further disfigure him into something even more unrecognizeable from his original form.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cranial_Clap_Trap: Skulls, it turns out, are a hindrance when one is attempting to chemically manipulate one's ogre.  Razzil has eliminated that obstruction.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Craniomancer: A round head is an abomination.  So too, a round back.  Dark Seer now sports the cranium most ideal in all the universe.  In a battle of wits and wills, the pointiest head will often prevaile.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Darkstar_the_Mistforged: This ancestral blade of House Avernus was cast into the Font, to be forged anew. What emerged was an amalgam of steel, and mist, that feasts upon the souls of its foes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dawn_of_the_Moon: On the night of each new moon, rites are sung and offerings burned in honor of the goddess of the moon, Selemene, in the hope that her countenance may shine once more. To wear the garb customary to these rituals is considered a sacred honor.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deadly_Gaming_Cup_Season_: 16 professional teams compete for the $10,000 prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deadwinter_Arms: After years of the frost stirring deep inside him it began to creep out, seeking to claim him as if it had a life of its own. Enchanted cloth on his arms are a last line of defense against the icy claws reaching towards Ethreain by the dangerous, otherworldly power within.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deadwinter_Back: Over time, the frost magic had birthed a powerful force within Ethreain. It began to florish and bloom, eventually maturing enough to manifest physically in the form of a dense crystal in his back. It continues to grow steadily and appears to reach, seeking to embrace the mage himself.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deadwinter_Belt: Mastery of certain magics come with a price. As Ethreain honed his skill and grew stronger he encased his legs in ice and gathered shards to shield him. His sash helps to balance the frost within so that it does not consume him.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deadwinter_Neck: His ascension to a new throne and reign of ice deserved fitting attire - Ethreain reclaimed his tattered cloak from the previous life and imbued it with a darkened frost-bound undead aura.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Death_Charge_Set:
It's a breakthrough.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Death_Mask_of_the_Conquer: Wear this mask, and it will be the last face your enemies ever see.

A terrifying combination of dark magic and science-gone-wrong, the bestial Deathripper is a boon to its master and a nightmare to all others.

Hailing from the Iron Kingdoms, the Deathripper is a deadly creation of the undead nation of Cryx, as seen in the epic tabletop miniatures game, WARMACHINE. For more information on WARMACHINE, visit www.privateerpress.com

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deep_Vault_Guardian_Spine: A guardian's spinal display serves as an identifier to his peers, and a warning to his foes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deep_Vault_Guardian_Tride: Few creatures of the deep are able to heft such a heavy weapon, let alone weild it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deep_Warden_Cape: There's not a lot to a darkray, but you'll find what's there to be pretty durable.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deep_Wardens_Impounded_Ho: They say the thief that used to own this hood killed eleven guards before he was finally sent up for air.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deep_Wardens_Tooth_Bracer: If you're going to go through all the trouble of breaking out of prison, you may as well take a few souvenirs!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deepest_Depths: Within the coldest depths one must be clever and adaptable, or become food for one that is.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Blade_of_Apocalypti: A cursed blade forged to slice through the membrane that separates the seven hells.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Blood_Armor: Heavy platemail forged in the blood of the Tarnsmen's dead gods.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Blood_Guard: When the Red Mist consumed the Thousand Tarns, the lakes turned red with the blood of the slain. Many demons masquerading as the lawmakers and priests of that doomed civilization were also destroyed, their blood mixing with that of the mortals they once ruled.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Blood_Helm: A helm bearing the cyclopean visage of the Tarnsmen's demonic war god. It is said the Red Mist destroyed the god and took its symbols for their own.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Claive: Sven seemed overcome with nostalgia at the sight of this sword, though he would not say why.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Eater: Shadow Fiend has long collected the souls of his enemies. As is the case with any collector, some prizes have stood above others, to be sought out at any cost. However, there are certain souls that should not be tried, and forces so dark and filled with rage that no being could hope to contain them. Thus did Shadow Fiend learn the price, and gift, that comes with stealing the souls of demons, and he was changed evermore.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Guise_of_the_Vandal: For a hundred years, a blind smeevil hammered and honed his masterpiece, until the great work was done.  None shall see your face behind the iron mask of the Demon Guise.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Quiver_of_the_Crypt: He's got eyes in the back of his back.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Shard: Shattered during the cataclysmic battle of Heaven's Gate, the Blade of Worlds fell as a thousand pieces. Smuggled back into the foundries of Hell, the largest fragment was later reformed, the runes upon its surface shifting to denote a new name, Demon Shard.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Skull_Staff: Witch Doctor clearly has a thing for skulls.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Spine_Recurve_Bow: Made from the vertebrae of the fallen damned, this bow is crooked as the spine of any demon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demonbag_of_the_Archivist: All Who Borrow Must Return is the Archivist's slogan. Those who do not return what they borrow are soon visited by that which resides in this bag.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demonhide_Girdle_of_Apoca: Doom's loins are girded in thickest demonhide and steel.

Double or right-click this tool and use it on an item in your backpack to give the item a customized description.

Description Tags are consumable items, and may only be used once. A described item can be reverted to its original state by right-clicking the item in the backpack and pressing the 'Restore' option.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Direstone_Crests: As the wave of Morphling crests, surging into battle, these Direstone crests come along for the ride.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Direstone_Liferipper: Direstone is said to be lightweight and easy to counterbalance, making it perfect for a reaper.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dolfrat_and_Roshinante: How did I get here? Such words of power are commonly heard from Dolfrat the Wizard, whose magic is so great that even he cannot grasp it. Indeed, his enemies accuse him of having no magical training whatsoever, pointing to the evidence of his most frequent incantation: Did I do that? And should you ever spy the mighty Dolfrat flat on his back in the road, you can be sure his trusty steed Roshinante is somewhere nearby--probably galloping at top speed away from a creaky tree or shadow that resembled a demon of nightmarish power.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dominator_of_the_Undersca: The Narrow Maze is lined with sharpened blades, but not the slightest scratch mars the surface of this hardened armor.
Energy seethes through Razor's garb, ready to feed his whip with lethal power.
Protects Razor's forearms from inadvertent backlash.
The twisted paths of the Narrow Maze are written on the inside of this mask, where Razor alone can study them.
No weapon is more feared by the involuntary inhabitants of the Underscape.

At its center yawns a great fissure, filled with the gravel remains of the countless many. Only a single segment of a single pillar remains to mark a grave for this ancient civilization.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Evil_Geniuses_Pennant: Show your support for a team by buying this Team Pennant! Pennants can be combined with other pennants to upgrade your Team Pennant fan level.  The level of your Team Pennant will increase the total fan value of the team when you are spectating a Tournament match.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FACEIT_Pro_League_Europe: FACEIT Pro League Europe is an elite community created by professional Dota2 players from EU. FPL is also a development centre for young talented players and future champions. You can qualify for FPL by playing on Master and Diamond League on FACEIT every month.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FACEIT_Pro_League_North_A: FACEIT Pro League North America is an elite community created by professional Dota2 players from NA. FPL is also a development centre for young talented players and future champions. You can qualify for FPL by playing on Master and Diamond League on FACEIT every month.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FACTME_Dota_2_Online_Tour: The FACTME Dota 2 Online Tournaments is a round-robin competition where the top 4 teams will advance to the playoffs. Teams are competing for a prize pool of 1,000 Pesos!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FES_League_Championship_K: The top 16 teams from around the United Kingdom will compete in this new UK Dota 2 League to become champions!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FGCL_CIS_Open_Cup: Open tournament where over 500 teams will fight for the championship and a prize of $1000.  Bundle includes ticket and the Sovereign of the Woodlands set!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FGCL_CIS_Open_Cup_Ticket: Open tournament where over 500 teams will fight for the championship and a prize of $1000.  This ticket only gives you access to view games in the WPL CIS: Open Cup.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FGCL_CIS_Open_Cup_Ticket_: Open tournament where over 500 teams will fight for the championship and a prize of $1000.  This ticket only gives you access to view games in the WPL: CIS Open Cup.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FGCL_Championship_League: Top 32 winners in the group stages will be competing for a prize pool of $1000! The winners get a place in FGCL StarSeries. Includes an exclusive in-game HUD Skin: Reign of Maelrawn!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FGCL_Fight_Club_Promote_S: Eight invited professional teams and eight qualifying teams compete in Promote Season of Fight Club for $1,000!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FJBEG_Dota_2_Tournament: 32 Teams in Indonesia will play in this tournament for 500$ ! and Sponsored by Biggest Online Casino In Indonesia.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FJBEG_Online_Tournament_#: 64 Teams in Indonesia will play in online tournament for Rp 10.000.000 prize pool. Presented by biggest transaction gaming equipment facebook forum in Indonesia and powered by 9nagabet.com (sports & live casino) !
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Faceless_Rex: In another time, in another place, perhaps Faceless Void would have rather carried items for heroes rather than become a hero himself. In another time, in another place, he might also have been a time-disrupting dinosaur. Who can say what other paths Faceless Void may have taken if given the chance...
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Falconers_Design_Set: Includes all of the items in the 'Falconer's Design' set for Windranger:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Falcons_Rise: The Skywrath revere all avian species, and hold the falcon in particularly high esteem.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fallen_Sword: The sword that burns and is not consumed.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Familiar_Woods: A trusted friend on a well-worn path.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Familiar_of_the_Great_Gre: As vicious as it is loyal, the familiar of the great grey is a powerful ally in any battle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Familiars_of_Glorious_Ins: Includes the Glorious Inspiration forge spirit ability icon
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fantasy_S2_Bronze_Telepor: A custom teleport effect given as a reward for placing third in a Fantasy Season 2 league.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fantasy_S2_Gold_Teleport: A custom teleport effect given as a reward for placing first in a Fantasy Season 2 league.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fantasy_S2_Silver_Telepor: A custom teleport effect given as a reward for placing second in a Fantasy Season 2 league.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fantasy_Season_1_Bronze_T: Prize for third place in a Fantasy Season 1 League
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fantasy_Season_1_Gold_Tro: Prize for winning a Fantasy Season 1 League
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fantasy_Season_1_Silver_T: Prize for second place in a Fantasy Season 1 League
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fantasy_Ticket_Season_1: This ticket will allow you to create a new Fantasy League or join an existing one in Fantasy Season 1.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fantasy_Ticket_Season_2: This ticket will allow you to create a new Fantasy League or join an existing one in Fantasy Season 2.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Faringame_League_Season_1: Best russian Far East teams compete for a 50000 ruble prize pool!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fashion_of_Yoskreth: The fashions of Yoskreth are not common in much of the rest of the world.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fashion_of_the_Scorching_: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Fashion of the Scorching Princess' set for Lina:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fatal_Blossom: Contains all of the items in the 'Fatal Blossom' item set for Death Prophet plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Father_of_the_Forest: Includes all of the items in the 'Father of the Forest' set for Nature's Prophet plus loading screen. The weapon includes an ambient particle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Faulds_of_the_Gwimyeon_Wa: Speed is always the warrior's ally.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Favor_of_the_Shades: A gift from the shades of fortune! Will something valuable be inside?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Favors_of_the_Shamanic_Li: He that speaketh for the Shades casts his own light.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Feathered_Naginata: A light spear, balanced for quick slashes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Featherfall: Arrows of a feather flock together. Constructed from strong and resilient harpy feathers, this set of Featherfall is a fine upgrade to Windranger's look.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Featherfall_Bow: A colorful bow adorned with tough harpy feathers is just what a feisty girl like Lyralei needs for fabulous mega-kills!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Featherfall_Cloak: A breezy, flowing cloak is just what one needs to look good on a hunting trip.  Particularly if your prey might be hunting you right back.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Featherfall_Locks: Hair tied up and out of the way, she tops it off with a feathery headscarf for a breezy, carefree, I-just-shot-you-in-the-face look.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Featherfall_Quiver: Made of finest rumble-hide, this low-hanging quiver of feathery arrows is ready for action!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Featherfall_Spaulders: Designed to camouflage her outline and confuse attackers, these shoulders of tough harpy feathers offer protection against whirling blades.  This is sure to turn some heads.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Featherhutch: Having grown tired of her dilapidated chicken hutch, Babka the Bewitcher cast an enchantment to spruce it up and give it some life. She should have made sure there wasn't a chicken inside before she cast the spell.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Federal_League_Season_1: The first season of the Federal League allows teams in Europe to compete in different divisions to become champions!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Female_Dota_2_Southeast_A: A three month long league with a single-elimination BO3 playoffs for the top 4 teams. FSL is open to female Dota 2 teams that play on the Southeast Asian server.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Femur_Thrasher: A sharp, cracked femur of some unidentifiable sea-beast.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fengyun_Tournament: This year's Fengyun Tournament features grassroots teams competing against top Asian Dota 2 powerhouses for a prize pool of 100,000 RMB.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fengyun_Tournament__ADMIN: This year's Fengyun Tournament features grassroots teams competing against top Asian Dota 2 powerhouses for a prize pool of 100,000 RMB.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fetish_of_the_Father_Spir: When it comes to dazzling fetishes, the Father Spirit knows best.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Feudal_Mace_of_Chivalry: Prove your chivalry by smashing enemies in the face with this powerful weapon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FezzleFeez_the_Magic_Carp: Fezzle-Feez, like most smeevils, has no floor on which to spread his magic carpet, therefore he unrolls it in mid-air.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fiery_Soul_of_the_Slayer: It has often been said that Lina's hair was touched by fire, though few know the truth of this claim.  In Lina's youth, as her natural talents first began to smoke and smolder it was her fiery hair that told the tale of the storm to come.  With time and training, her skill and control of the flame was enough to suppress the searing display.  Yet on occasion, when her ire grows and tempers flare, the full measure of Lina's burning spirit threatens to unleash its wrath.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fiery_Ward_of_Eki_Bukaw: With this fiery ward, no secrets are safe, no location hidden, no weakness unexposed.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fin_Kings_Charm: Though once used by the Fin King's arcanists to dispatch his foes to the underwater realm, the core technique of the charm has since been lost, and much of its potency along with it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Finblade: Kunkka's ship cleaves the waves as easily as Finblade cleaves his enemies. Kunkka revels in the iridescent play of light given off by dashing spray and liberated souls alike.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fine_Bone_Bracers: Bracers crafted from the fine bone of some alien beast.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Finnish_Dota_League: The first season of the Finnish Dota 2 League provides Finnish teams a platform to develop Finnish eSports to the next level!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FireBlessed_Mail_of_the_D: Includes all of the items in the 'Fire-Blessed Mail of the Drake' set for Dragon Knight:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fire_Dragon_of_Doom: Includes all of the items in the 'Fire Dragon of Doom' set for Dragon Knight:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fire_of_the_Exiled_Ronin: The flames of the Ronin burn hot against all who oppose him.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fireborn_Odachi: Forged in the fires that bubbled up from the sea on the night your homeland sank beneath the waves!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Firebreather_of_the_Voyag: Carried mainly for show, Kunkka does find Firebreather's flintlock a reliable means of lighting his pipe in inclement weather.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fires_of_Vashundol: Contains all of the items in the 'Fires of Vashundol' set for Doom plus ambient particles and loading screen. Created in partnership with Evil Geniuses, who receive a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Firestarter: Contains all of the items in the 'Firestarter' set for Batrider plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FirstGameTV_Dota_2_Cup_To: Contains the FirstGame Dota 2 Cup Ticket and the Rhinoceros Order set for Sven
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_First_Arrival_Dota_2_Tour: A double elimination tournament where teams will compete for treasure keys in Dota 2!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fishing_Halberd: Off the coast near the village of Pole are fish large enough to eat a man in a single bite.  Against such a beast, a spear simply will not do.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fishy_Frillhawk: In Dark Reef Prison, Slark kept too low a profile to ever be called a trendsetter. He figured nobody noticed his radical look. But as soon as he had broken out, the remaining inmates began to imitate this finny style.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fistful_of_Snowballs: Just when they least expect it... Snowball fight!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flail_Sleek: Many lives has this mighty flail ended.  Many skulls has this mighty flail pulped.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flail_of_the_Death_Charge:
Your iron flail shall break them.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flail_of_the_Great_Elder: The title of Brewmaster is won in combat. This ancient weapon is also passed with the title.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flail_of_the_Iron_Will: Shimmering with an elder power, one swing is enough to dim even the stoutest heart.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flame_Bat: The Flame Bat's blood is as thick as tar and burns just as hot.The rider taps the creature's blood, harvesting it for his own fiery needs.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flamestitched_Suitings_Ba: Do you know how hard it is to find a fireproof bandanna?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flamestitched_Suitings_Se: Includes all of the items in the 'Flamestitched Suitings' set for Batrider:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flamestitched_Suitings_Wr: You mix it right, the world burns.  You mix it wrong, it burns a bit brighter!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flaming_Scepter_of_Ancest: By rights it came to Aggron, and by luck it happened to be on fire!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flared_Wooden_Crest: A simple, but decorative crest of wood. Designed to provide protection from the hated axe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flares_of_the_Solar_Divin: The heat of the eastern wastes is said to be extraordinary.  One must dress appropriately.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flight_of_the_Marauding_P: Contains the Flight of the Marauding Pyro set for Batrider, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flight_of_the_Sparrowhawk: Includes all of the items in the 'Flight of the Sparrowhawk' set for Windranger:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flight_of_the_Valkyrie: This bundle contains all of the items for the 'Flight of the Valkyrie' set for Legion Commander.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flourishing_Lodestar: In the shade of the first trees, water runs clear, and the earth radiates a gentle warmth. The spirits of the verdant wild coil about, endlessly mending, and eternally twisting old life into new. From the boughs of these elder saplings was carved the Lodestar, a tool to aid nature's benevolent servants so that they may guide, heal, and preserve all that must be held dear.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flower_Staff_of_the_Peace: A Candral-Flower plucked from the heart of the Endless Copse.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flowering_Treant: What appears to be a beautiful blossom is in fact the motile form of a cordyceps fungus which has infested the poor plant. It is still under the control of Nature's Prophet, but the ultimate outcome for the infected treant is far from pleasant.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flowersong_Tempest: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Flowersong Tempest' set for Windranger plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flowing_Entropy: Contains all of the items in the 'Flowing Entropy' set for Spectre plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fluted_Guard_of_the_Moon_: An emblem of honor, worn with grace but never lightly.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fluted_Guard_of_the_Sword: The sheer size and weight of this piece were scoffed at until Sven used the shoulder spikes to impale an attacking ogre along the Feral Road.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fluttering_Staff: So gentle was the prophet that when he pulled the branch to make this staff, the butterflies upon the leaves remained. Includes ambient particle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flux_Dota_2_Tournament: Flux Dota 2 Tournament is a Dota 2 Competition consisting of 64 teams competing for a prize pool of over $950!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Focal_Resonance: Within the Violet Archives are blueprints for weapons that many would say should remain forgotten. Such a weapon is the Focal, which resonates with, and channels the wearer's psyche into a blast of piercing power.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Focus_of_Resonant_Vibranc: To focus and bend the wild, unseen energies to one's whim is a skill few possess!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Force_Staff: Sometimes a little push is all you need.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Forest_Hermit_Set: Includes all the items in the Forest Hermit set for Earthshaker.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Foretellers_Robes_Set: Contains all of the items in the 'Foreteller's Robes' set for Death Prophet:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Forge_of_Iron_Will:
An iron mask for an iron will.

These items commemorate the release of Valve's documentary, Free to Play, and were created in partnership with Fear, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Forgemasters_Hammer: The only day Axe declared defeat was the day he tried to forge a weapon with an axe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Forgemasters_Mask: The warriors of the Red Mist are not only superb fighters, but also master smiths. Each grunt is expected to craft his own sword and his own shield. Should his war tools fail him on the battlefield, the grunt has only his own hands to blame.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Form_of_the_Atniw: No foe shall stand against the true form!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Form_of_the_Great_Grey: A form out of your worst nightmares.  The wolf is at your door.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Form_of_the_Great_Grey_Se: A wolf in warrior's clothing.  This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Form of the Great Grey' set for Lycan:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Form_of_the_Onyx_Grove: Among the northern pine did Sylla discover the darkness of the Onyx Grove, where creatures both fierce and strange gather to quarrel.  In time, the lone druid adapted his own form to join in the fray.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Formed_Alloy_Apron:
If you're going bring in a dragon to help you mix alloys you'd best become fireproof!

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Formed_Alloy_Blades:
Invaluable and nigh indestructible, it can take up to fourteen months to mix materials to concoct just one pound of shadeglass.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Formed_Alloy_Flask:
Keeping a splash of dragon drool on hand is never a bad idea, assuming you can find the right mix of alloys to store it!

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Formed_Alloy_Goggles:
A shadeglass eyepiece is a perfect addition to any laboratory.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Formed_Alloy_Pauldrons:
Plates of steel with a trim is made of nickel-titanium. Ultimately, the dragon's teeth on the shoulders are just for looks.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Formed_Alloy_Set:
Give 'em the old one-two!

These items were created in partnership with Alliance, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Formed_Alloy_Wristplates:
Never underestimate the usefulness of an angry dragon's flamegland when designing new metals!

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Forsaken_Beauty_Set: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Forsaken Beauty' set for Medusa:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fortune_of_Three_Spirits_: Contains all of the items in the 'Strength of the Demon Stone', 'Flames of Prosperity', and the 'Gifts of Fortune' for the Three Spirits. Also includes a bonus loading screen and HUD.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Forward_to_victory: 32 teams from the CIS Region will compete for the $10 prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Forward_to_victory_cup#2: 32 teams from the CIS will battle for a prize of 100$
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Foulfell_Shard: A fragment of black crystal that radiates corrupting, abyssal energy. It throbs with the voiceless hatred of demons imprisoned within.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FourFangs_the_Swordbreake: The fangs of this fierce blade bite deep into your foe's bared weapon!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fractal_Shard_of_Inner_Ab: Deep in the hell of Hell, Terrorblade lay bound behind fractal walls, sentenced to an eternity of twisted contemplation. He stared long into the reflection of his own worst self. And long did his worst self stare into him. Now they rise together, a single entity more powerful than ever before.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fragbite_Masters: 32 teams compete in the Fragbite Masters which is an online tournament with a $30,900 prize pool for Dota 2.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fragbite_Masters_2014: Fragbite Masters 2014 consists of twelve professional teams competing alongside a bracket open to amateur teams for a prize pool of over 200,000 SEK.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fragment_of_Radiant_Ore: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. This treasure contains full item sets.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Free_Treasure_Redemption: Right click and redeem this item to exchange it for a free treasure of your choice.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Free_to_Play_Collectors_P:
These items commemorate the release of Valve's 'Free to Play' documentary. A portion of the purchase will go toward the players featured in the film - Danil 'Dendi' Ishutin, Clinton 'Fear' Loomis and Benedict 'hyhy' Lim.

The bundle includes all of the items in the 'Forge of Iron Will' set for Sven, the 'Murder of Crows' set for Pudge, the 'Crown of Hells' set for Doom and the exclusive 'Wide Angle' Ward, 'Filmtail' Courier and 'Depth of Field' HUD:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Free_to_Play_Courier: This courier commemorates the release of Valve's documentary 'Free to Play'.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Free_to_Play_HUD: This HUD commemorates the release of Valve's documentary 'Free to Play'.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Free_to_Play_Ward: This ward commemorates the release of Valve's documentary 'Free to Play'.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Freestyle_Dota_1x1: Players from Kramatorsk will fight for a prize.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Friend_of_the_West: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Friend of the West' set for Beastmaster:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Avalanche: Some say the garment began as the wedding gown of an ancient queen.  Others say it was once a battle cloak of a frost ogre. In truth, the enchanted fabric is as malleable as an avalanche, and can mold itself into various forms. This form has attracted a lone wolf pup, who has now become a hardy and loyal companion.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Avalanche_Bundle: Contains the 'Frost Avalanche' arcana for Crystal Maiden.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Owls_Beacon: Little hope remains to those lost in the frozen north, yet it is said that those able to summon an elusive Frost Owl will always find their way to safety.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Shard_Armlets: Coming through! Even Juggernaut will leap to avoid the icy edges of these lethal armlets.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Shard_Crown: Morphling spent eternities travelling space in the form of ice. Morphling knows ice. You know that if Morphling wears a crown of ice, it is a serious crown.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Shard_Pauldrons: The glitter of the interstellar ice that once bedizened Morphling, decks his shoulders now as he surges to and fro across the field of battle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Spikes: A playful crop of spikes that says 'I'm killing you and having fun doing it.' Includes a frost-tinged cloak to complete the image.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Spikes_FIXUP_BUNDLE: Use this bundle to unpack the Frost Spikes and Ice Burst Cloak items. These were previously one item, but have been broken into two.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Touched_Cleaver: A deep winter chill touches this cleaver for Tusk!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostbitten_Cloak_of_the_: Ice is nice!  Except in cases of frostbite, so stay warm in this downy cape.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Raider_Axe: The blacksmithing skill of the Frostiron Tribe has kept many a foe at bay.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Raider_Cape: As Ymir wandered the great northern wilderness, he spent time among the Frostiron Tribe.  Upon his departure, he was given gifts to remember them by.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Raider_Fist: Deceptively light yet incredibly durable, this glove was gifted to Tusk with the hope that it might ensure Ymir's safe return.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Raider_Helm: Denizens of the northern sea, the Frostiron Tribe are a proud people with a rich history.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Raider_Set: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Frostiron Raider' set for Tusk:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Raider_Shield: During his stay with the Frostiron Tribe, Ymir tried his hand at crafting armor.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Raider_Tusks: Masters of metals, the artisans of the Frostiron Tribe crafted steel tusks for Ymir as a symbol of his bravery.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Sorceress_Brooc: The brooch is made of glacial sapphire carved by the artisans of the Frostiron tribe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Sorceress_Cape: A tribe unknown to much of the world, the Frostiron are able to weave fabrics of incredible durability and warmth.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Sorceress_Cuffs: As fleeting spring came to the icy north, Ymir set off into the wilderness.  The warm seasons passed, and when winter returned so did he, bringing with him gifts and tales of a hidden tribe living near the coast.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Sorceress_Pads: The pads are deceptively durable, able to deflect even the strongest blow.  Such is the skill of the Frostiron Tribe that they remain as light as a snowflake.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Sorceress_Set: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Frostiron Sorceress' set for Crystal Maiden:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Sorceress_Staff: The cool glow of an uncut glacial sapphire symbolizes the icy resolve of the Frostiron Tribe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostivus_Gift__Naughty: A gift for saving Frostivus from the Greevils! What could be inside? It is a mystery. This gift looks like a Greevil sat on it or maybe chewed it up.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostivus_Gift__Nice: A gift for saving Frostivus from the Greevils! What could be inside? It is a mystery. This particular gift looks to be in excellent condition.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostivus_HUD_Skin: A chill fills the air as the snows blanket the cold ground.  The time of Frostivus comes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostivus_Treasure_Key: Used to open locked <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Chests</font>. Double click or right-click the key in your backpack and select the chest you want to open.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frosty_Treasure_of_Frosti: You will need <font color='#9da1a9'>Frostivus 2013 Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Beware! At the end of <font color='#9da1a9'>January 12, 2014</font> this chest will crumble into useless snowflakes. This chest contains one of several mysterious new items:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frozen_Feather_Set: Includes all of the items in 'Frozen Feather' set for Crystal Maiden:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frozen_Formation: If you're spotted, it would be in your best interest not to freeze!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frozen_Star: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Frozen Star' set for Lich:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frozen_Stein_of_the_Bar_B: There's always time for a frosty mug!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frozen_Touch: There is cold wisdom in the core of winter.
