Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mantle_of_Eldritch_Ice: The ice mage's robes became the Lich's tattered shroud. Superstitious subjects hammered spikes of sacred metal as a warning into the dead mage's skull, none suspecting that upon his resurrection he would wear the device as a cursed crown of domination.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mantle_of_Endless_Havoc: Heavy is the burden of unending war, yet many are its vicious pleasures.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mantle_of_Hells_Ambassado: Suggestive of the robes of office of some infernal dignitary, the cape was an honorific bestowed on Lion by a grateful demon populace.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mantle_of_Mysteries: None know whose bones line mantle's fringe.  Every teller must ask unanswerable questions.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mantle_of_the_Acolyte_of_: Travelling between dimensions, followers of Clasz require protection from the chill interstitial spaces.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mantle_of_the_Blood_Coven: By the mantle of the Flayed Ones shall your enemies know you.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mantle_of_the_Crescent_Mo: Plaid with moth wings and dressed with armour made from pure Moonsilver. A vestment like this is both rare and magical as it grants its wearer with the boon of increased agility.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mantle_of_the_Crested_Can:
Upon the shoulders of the cannoneer lie the fate of their fleet and fellows.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mantle_of_the_Cruel_Magic:
The quest for knowledge oft leads down dark paths.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mantle_of_the_Iron_Will: Against his shoulders does the world shatter.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mark_of_the_Mistral_Fiend: Includes all of the items in the 'Mark of the Mistral Fiend' set for Abaddon plus a loading screen and ability icons.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mark_of_the_Subtle_Demon: One must not balk at death.  One must learn to face all trials.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mark_of_the_Taunting_Swin: Spoon built a special sign to warn people away from where they intended to test the Swine cannon. Of course, they never got around to testing the cannon in the first place.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Markswomans_Cap: Having a bad hair day?  No problem.  This snappy little markswoman's cap is stylish for all occasions.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_MarsTV_Dota_Elite_Invitat: The first and second places from CN Qualifer for the International will face up four invited Chinese top teams in Huaxi, the top village in China.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mask_of_Dark_Ferocity: In the bounty hunting business, a little intimidation can go a long way.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mask_of_Distant_Sands: The heat of the eastern wastes is said to be extraordinary.  One must cover themselves appropriately.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mask_of_Fury: Your face is masked but your fury won't be.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mask_of_Inscrutable_Zeal: While not as sturdy as a proper dueling mask, this covering is better tuned to project words of power.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mask_of_a_Thousand_Faces: A ceremonial mask worn on special occasions. This must be a special occasion.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mask_of_the_Crimson_Cutth: The contract for the head of the Crimson Cut-throat was one of the most difficult that Gondar had ever accepted.  It was only natural that he'd keep a few souvenirs.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mask_of_the_Divine_Sorrow: Has the Mask, Hood and Crown styles.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mask_of_the_Freelancer: This old gladiatorial helm serves Sven well as he travels the land in search of honor and gold.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mask_of_the_ManySighted: On the Isle of Masks, death is said to have many watchful eyes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mask_of_the_Tahlin_Watch: The crest of the Tahlin Watch sits upon the brow.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mask_of_the_ThiefScholar: Just as what is known must be learned, what is spoken must be thought.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Masked_Fey_:
Noble by nature, Masked Fey overcame centuries of solitude to become guardian of the skies.

Includes alternate color styles.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Masked_Fey_Courier_and_Sc: Includes Masked Fey courier and loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Masks_of_Ancestral_Luck: The names of the twin leaders who once owned these masks have been lost to ignorance.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Master_Artificers_Hammer: A powerful enchanted hammer used to extract Prismatic and Ethereal gems. This item will destroy the item it is used on.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Master_Assassins_Grim_Cut: The forked tip allows the wielder to pry back any armor the target may be wearing.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Master_Assassins_Mancatch: Designed to catch and hold the target, no matter which point is used.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Master_Assassins_Mask: The cloth is treated with oils and wax to stave off enemy poisons.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Master_Assassins_Shoulder: Built to deflect enemy weapons, the shoulder plates are carefully tailored to the wearer.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Master_Assassins_Shuriken: The blade end and grip are carefully balanced to sail through the air accurately, and with ease.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Master_Assassins_Tails: The trailing cloth obscures the assassin's form and, in a pinch, can be used to thwart enemy blades.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Master_Gaming_Series_Dota: This two-series tournament has the largest prize pool in Indonesia. The top teams from the region compete for the 100,000,000 IDR prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Master_League: Master League tournament teams Peru where beginners start looking for new challenges.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Master_Weaver_Set: Includes all the items in the Master Weaver set for Weaver.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mattock_of_Distortion: One blow of this mighty mallet, and waves of time-warping distortion spread to erase his enemies from existence.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Maw_of_the_Devourer: From the World at the Rim, this staff is a weighty reminder of the howling void that waits for us all.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Maze_of_Anguish: To be wrapped in her wings is to be trapped in her web.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mazoku_League: Some of the best teams in South America face off to prove themselves as the best amateur team in the region.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Meadows_Mercy: Though the forest itself may be neutral, this spear will bring a swift end to those who dare disturb the creatures who call it home.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Meat_Dragger: Sometimes the meat won't go nowhere unless you drag it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mecha_Boots_of_Travel_Mk_: Why rely on uncertain sorcery when an unstable machine can be just as dangerous? Painstakingly reconstructed from half-remembered schematics, the transdimensional technologies built into these boots is theorized to have caused the Violet Plateau Incident. Of course, that couldn't possibly happen again. Er, could it?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mechjaw_the_Boxhound: Between their experiments in transdimensional science, a pair of engineers in the facility atop the Violet Plateau designed a device to store and protect their most valuable valuables. Had those engineers not been eaten by indescribable horrors, they surely would have become rich!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_MegaKills_Axe: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the resonant booms of Axe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_MegaKills_Bastion: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the smooth worldly tones of Bastion's narrator, also known as Rucks.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_MegaKills_Bristleback: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the rough-and-tumble wit of Bristleback. Granted exclusively to owners of 2015's Compendium for The International.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_MegaKills_Clockwerk: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the metal moxie of Clockwerk.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_MegaKills_Defense_Grid: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the upbeat wisdom of Defense Grid's very own General Fletcher.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_MegaKills_GLaDOS: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the withering sarcasm and passive-aggressive taunting of Portal's GLaDOS, science fiction's deadliest insult A.I.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_MegaKills_Juggernaut: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the enthusiastic shouts of the traveling warrior, Juggernaut.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_MegaKills_Lina: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the fiery attitude of Lina.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_MegaKills_Natures_Prophet: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the wild cries of Nature's Prophet.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_MegaKills_Pirate_Captain: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the drunken antics of a scurvy-ridden Pirate Captain.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_MegaKills_Pyrion_Flax: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the unique and unruly humor of Dota 2 satirist Pyrion Flax.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_MegaKills_Stanley_Parable: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the sardonically meta wit of the Narrator from The Stanley Parable.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_MegaKills_Storm_Spirit: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the joyful exposition of Storm Spirit.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_MegaKills_Techies: This item replaces the Default announcer with the explosive enthusiasm of Spoon of Techies Demolitions.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_MegaKills_Trine: This item replaces the Mega-Kills announcer with the soothing tones of Trine's tale-weaving narrator.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mega_Gamer_UTFPR_2015: An amateur championsip where the best teams from the south of Brazil fight for honor and almost $1000 in prizes!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Megalodon_Cup_Season_1: The Megalodon Cup features the top 8 teams from Brazil competing for a total prize of R$1,000!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Megalodon_Cup_Season_1__A: The Megalodon Cup features the top 8 teams from Brazil competing for a total prize of R$1,000!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Megalodon_Cup_Season_2: The top 16 teams in South America compete in the second seasno of the Megalodon Cup for R$1200! Bundle includes the Temple of the Sacred Memories HUD skin and loading screen!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Megalodon_Cup_Season_2_Ti: The top 16 teams in South America compete in the second season of the Megalodon Cup for R$1200! This ticket only gives you access to view games in the Megalodon Cup Season 2.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Megalodon_Starters_League: Teams participate in the first season of the Megalodon Starters League for cash and hardware prizes!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mei_Nei_Jade_Rabbit_Bundl: Contains the Mei Nei Jade Rabbit courier and loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mei_Nei_the_Jade_Rabbit: As eternal as the moon, Mei Nei fearlessly traverses the fields of battle in order to replenish the weary and wounded.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Meister_Dota_2_Captain_Dr: Meister Dota 2 Captain Draft Tournament is a Dota 2 Captain Draft Competition between 64 teams in the region competiting for a prizepool of over $700.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Meister_Series_League: A mini tournament by The Bomb Squad Esports event organizer with prize pool 3.000.000 IDR, Supported by AccentlTV and The Wolf. There are a rising stars teams who agains each another to be number one in Indonesia.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mentor_of_the_High_Plains: Contains all of the items in the 'Mentor of the High Plains' set for Ember Spirit plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Meranth_Executioners_Blad: A single edged blade perfect for quickly removing heads. Or legs. Or arms.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Merciless_Spear: Built to strike into the core of an adversary, and tear it apart when withdrawn.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mercurials_Call:
Across time and space, the Spectre known as Mercurial has struggled to be understood. Now the full nature of her violent wrath can be heard.
	Granted exclusively to owners of the 2014 Compendium for The International.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Merry_Wanderers_Brush: Beneath the magic moonless night sprout sights rare-seen by mortal man: the swaying sweep of faerie flight unfurls to gorgeous shimmering span. And from this beauteous wonder light of shifting hue there might be spied, yet those who seek such perilous views may oft then find their lives denied.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Metal_Horns: In a time long forgotten, a grateful king once gifted the Prophet these horns as thanks for aid of the forest.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mexican_Cup: The top teams from Meixco are invited to prove they are the top team from the region.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Midas_Knuckles: Midas has long been considered Alchemy's most successful practitioner. Seeking to address the incredible costs of war, he developed a series of gauntlet prototypes to be worn by revered knights of the kingdom, which were capable of minting coin with every strike.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Might_of_the_Old_World: A helm forged of enchanted alloys deep in the Astral plane, so that Elder Titan might better channel his Sprit and control both aspects of his broken soul.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Might_of_the_Slithereen_K: With this sword, truly, no Slithereen may fail.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mighty_Boar: This boar has a crazed look in his eye. Is it distrust? Madness? Or does he just want to eat your tangos.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Milan_Dota_2_League: The first season of the Milan Dota 2 league.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Militant_Cup_Season_1: The first season of Militant Cup series. 32 teams from CIS will compete each other. The winner will receive prize money upon victory!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mind_Piercer_of_the_Preda: Nyx's words enter the mind with great subtlety.  His horn enters the mind with considerably less subtlety.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mineski_ProGaming_League_: Mineski-Events Team proudly presents the 7th season of the Mineski Pro-Gaming League. Witness intense Dota 2 action as teams from all over the Philippines battle for the right to be named as the best in the country and a share from the initial prize pool of PHP 840,000.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Miracle_Tournament_Season: 32 Indonesian amateur teams will compete each other for 3.200.000 IDR Prize pool!!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mischievous_Dragon: Contains all of the items in the 'Mischievous Dragon' set for Puck plus a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mistblade: Forged in the Font of Avernus, and filled with a dark thirst.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mistbreaker: Second of the three house blades of Avernus.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mistral_Braid: The wind that gently tousles her locks, gives unmatched flight to Windranger's arrows.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mistress_of_the_Slitheree: My Mistress, your Master, sings Naga as her enemies bow, never to rise.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mnemonus_Arcanus_Set: Includes all of the items in the 'Mnemonus Arcanus' set for Invoker:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Modestly_Braided_Beard: Even for the Avatars of Immortals modesty is sometimes called for.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mok: One of the wildest beasts of the escaped menagerie that ran amok during the fall of Slom, this wily mandrill took Mok for his name, thinking the citizenry's cries of warning were a herald of his arrival.  Now he puts his mischievous nature to good use, wading into any chaotic situation in order to bring you what you need.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Moldering_Mask_of_Ka: Includes custom particle and custom ability icon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Molten_Claw: In a rush to lay his enemies down, Axe burst into a forge to scrounge for suitable armor. What he found was still fresh from the fire, which suited Axe just fine. Includes ambient particle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Molten_Fracture: Doom's power has shattered this blade.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Molten_Genesis: It takes a truly special bow to be wielded by fingers of flame.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Monarch_Bow: A relic from a hegemony long since passed, the Monarch rewards those who value lethal precision and skill over blunt force. As graceful in action as at rest, it complements perfectly the coolest of heads under the deadliest of circumstances.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Monstrous_Reprisal: Contains all of the items in the 'Monstrous Reprisal' set for Riki plus loading screen, ability icons and an autograph. These items were created in partnership with VeRsuta, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Montenegro_National_Leagu: Montenegro National League is the first professional Dota 2 league in Montenegro organized by Montenegro E-Sports Association. The best teams from country will compete for the championship and prizes!
Another season of Montenegro National League is coming with bigger and better prize pool. Who will become new masters of Montenegrin Dota 2 scene?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Monty: A sophisticate vagabond of the highest order, Monty would look down his nose at you if he had one.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Moon_Griffon:
On a night of a crescent moon, Mirana found a griffin cub in the maze of Nightsilver woods. Now the strange little beast is eager to serve his mistress.

This item includes custom Leap sound, idle and loadout animations.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Moon_Rift: Contains all of the items in the 'Moon Rift' item set for Mirana plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Moon_Rift_Style: Has two styles, Mask and No Mask
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Moonfall: When Nightsilver Wood was yet but a thicket, a shard of stellar origin fell. Around this holy landing was built the Shrine of Selemene, and the shard itself fashioned into the most sacred of arms possessed of the order of the Dark Moon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Morcant: This pale creature found its way down the starlight path as if it heard its future mistress calling.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Moroks_Mechanical_Mediary: Don't let its metal form deceive you: this contraption is more magic than machine. Fashioned by the Mad Mage Morok who was far too lazy to carry his own spell books and far too cheap to retain hirlings.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mortar_Forge: Contains all of the items in the 'Mortar Forge' set for Clockwerk plus a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mountain_Splitter: Usually used only by the Sagesmiths of Vuur, the stone antlers of the Murex elk are one of few tools capable of grasping the burning heartflint of the Vuurcrag mountains.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mountain_Trail_Challenge: The MTC is a proffesional tournament in which some of the best teams known will be invited to compete against each other.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mousesports_Pennant: Show your support for a team by buying this Team Pennant! Equip it in the 'fan slot' of your Player Loadout to show other spectators who you're rooting for. Upgrade it to show you mean business! In addition, equipping a pennant makes you eligible for item drops while you spectate your team's matches live during Valve supported tournaments.  Pennants can be combined with other pennants to upgrade your Team Pennant fan level.  The level of your Team Pennant will increase the total fan value of the team when you are spectating a Tournament match.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Muh_Keen_Gun: Not content to kill things one bullet at a time, Sniper commissioned the best gunsmith in the land to construct him a firearm worthy of his talented trigger finger.  Lovingly designed and crafted with all the skill and attention to detail befitting a master smithy of the keen, the weapon that resulted is truly one for the ages.  It's a bit on the heavy side, true, but not when balanced against the weight of corpses it will produce.  Hernia not included.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mulan_girls_team_league: A series of various events held in the Mulan girl’s team league.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Murder_of_Crows:
Shoulda' kept your beak out of this.

These items commemorate the release of Valve's documentary, Free to Play, and were created in partnership with Dendi, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Murrissey_the_Smeevil: It is rare to find a smeevil far from the warmth of the forge to which it's bound, for they thrive on the affectionate cuffings and curses of their sworn smith. But the lure of a free tortoiceros ride compelled the smeevil Murrissey to break every oath...
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mysterious_Egg: A hard, scaled egg that seems to be alive and almost ready to hatch. It hungers for the magical energies contained in Diretide essences. What comes out will be determined by the type and amount of magic the egg consumes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mysterious_Vagabonds_Conc: Although some travelling shaman have been rightly accused of selling colored water as if it were a certain cure for all ills, Rhasta makes no such claims and has never charged so much as a pence for a swig from this bottle. In fact, no one but Rhasta may drink from it. The Shadow Shaman's brew is certain death to anyone but its maker.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mysterious_Vagabonds_Hat: A shaman must take good care of his skin! Rhasta's master instructed. Therefore, always wear a hat to keep off the sun, and no less the evil influence of the moon. And then the old man always broke into laughter. And if you believe that, I have a bag of herbs here that will confer infinite wealth and immortality.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mysterious_Vagabonds_Pack: His old master said, Be clear what you are about, for these simple village folk read menace and evil intent into poor communication. Therefore Rhasta created a simple visual menu of the services he offers, and wears it in plain sight.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mysterious_Vagabonds_Wand: A final twist of the serpent completes Rhasta's disguise, in case he is travelling incognito. It must be admitted that sometimes he wields it just because he likes the companionship.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Mystic_Instruments_of_Tan: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Mystic Instruments of Tang-Ki' set for Shadow Shaman plus a loading screen:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NACDEC: The Chinese Dota Elite Community invades North America! This in-house league lets players compete every 2 weeks in competitive Dota 2!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NADotA_Elite_League_Febru: The most talented players in North America compete in the classic inhouse league format.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NADotA_Elite_League_Janua: The most talented players in North America compete in the classic inhouse league format.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NADota_Elite_League: The most talented players in North America compete for 8 weeks culminating in a 4-team double elimination all-star tournament. 50% of ticket profits go straight to the prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NADota_Elite_League_Augus: The most talented players in North America compete in the classic inhouse league format for four weeks.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NADota_Elite_League_Seaso: NADota Elite League returns for its second season! The most talented teams in North America compete in the classic league format for eight weeks, culminating in a 4-team double elimination all-star tournament. $3,000 prize pool, 400+ games guaranteed. Hosted by IXDL. Broadcast by NEO Dota.
The most talented players in North America compete in the classic in-house league format.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NADota_Elite_League_Septe: The most talented players in North America compete in the classic in-house league format for four weeks.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NCups_Season_1: 16 amateur teams will compete for the prize of 1000 rubles.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NCups_Season_2: Amateur teams from Russia and CIS countries will fight for the first place and the title of NCups Champions.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NEL_April_2015: The most talented players in North America compete in the classic inhouse league format.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NEL_March_2015: The most talented players in North America compete in the classic inhouse league format.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NEL_May_2015: The most talented players in North America compete in the classic inhouse league format.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NFCups_Season_1: 32 amateur teams from Russia and CIS countries will fight for the first place and the title of NFCups Champions
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NN_Dota_2_League_Season_2: The second season of NN Dota 2 league will gather many teams from CIS, which will compete for a cash prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NN_Dota_2_League_Season_3: The third season of NN Dota 2 league will gather many teams from the CIS, to compete for a cash prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NRS_GAMING_ONLINE_TOURNAM: 1st Online Tournament By NRS GAMING Where team will compete for a prize of 1.500.000 Rupiah
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NURE_Challenge_for_Studen: A league open to all students in Kharkov
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NaVi_Pennant: Show your support for a team by buying this Team Pennant! Equip it in the 'fan slot' of your Player Loadout to show other spectators who you're rooting for. Upgrade it to show you mean business! In addition, equipping a pennant makes you eligible for item drops while you spectate your team's matches live during Valve supported tournaments.  Pennants can be combined with other pennants to upgrade your Team Pennant fan level.  The level of your Team Pennant will increase the total fan value of the team when you are spectating a Tournament match.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NaVis_Weaselcrow: Fur and feather, beak and fang, Weaselcrow is just the thing!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Nails_in_the_Mad_Harveste: If there's a better way to keep a shoulder together, I ain't heard it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Name_Tag:
Double or right-click this tool and use it on an item in your backpack to give the item a customized name.

Name Tags are consumable items, and may only be used once. A named item can be reverted to its original state by right-clicking the item in the backpack and pressing the 'Restore' option.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_National_Esports_League: 32 teams will compete in the first season of the National Esport League in the Dota 2 Super Cup for $250!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Nature: In the verdant spring grows deep-rooted strength.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Natures_Grip: A well-seasoned staff, suited to the hoary wisdom of a woodland prophet.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Natures_Outcast_Horns: Ever in bloom are the horns of the wandering prophet.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Natures_Prophet_Announcer: This pack replaces the Default announcer and Mega-Kills announcer with the stern voice of Nature's Prophet.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Natures_Shortbow: Short in size, but long on killing power, this little bow is an ideal weapon for dispatching overconfident enemies.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Naval_Mine: When it fell to the depths and smashed a favorite coral bed, the Tidehunter swore to reunite the device with its owner.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Necklace_of_Scarlet_Raven: The sacred bird wheels above the altar of the Flayed Twins.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Necklace_of_the_Wildwings: The Wildwing are fierce and territorial, but they more than tolerate Enchantress in their realms: They welcome her.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Necropolis: Those long buried hold power long forgotten.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_NeoGAF_Dota_2_Inhouse_Lea: An amateur league for Neogaffers and others to play in a pseudo-competitive team-based (and friendly!) environment.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Neolution_GosuCup: Neolution GosuCup is a monthly cup where 4 of the top Asian teams compete for a prize pool of $1000. This cup runs for 5 months and is hosted by GosuGamers.net.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Neptunian_Sabre: It is said that Kunkka compelled Keen artisans to make this sabre from the salvage of vanquished Cataract Demons that were washed upon the shores of Keen homelands. It is speculated that he split the sea in half with it to locate Maelrawn the Tentacular and sever one of Its tentacles as a testament of his triumph against the Demons of Cataract. Wielding it with brute force and sea-hardened will, he now splits apart his enemies in torrents of sea blue and crimson red.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Nether_Lords_Regalia_Set:

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sable_Cup_2015__Defense_o: The Sable Cup is a Defense of the Australians non-professional DotA tournament focused to play in a competitive environment for Australian and New Zealand amateur Dota 2 teams.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sack_of_Scrolls: With this sacred item, your next battle is in the bag.  Also, some scrolls.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacral_Apparel: The shrunken skull of the warrior who killed the first Tale-Teller has found a special place of honor with all Tellers since.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Bones_Bracers: The runes upon the cuffs confer strength and courage upon the wearer.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Bones_Helmet: The warriors of the Dezun Order hold dear the bones of those whose sacrifice has come before.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Bones_Offhand_Weap: The bones of the earth that make the blade of this dagger are no less sacred than the warrior who once held it.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Orb_Carapace: Once in a thousand cyclings of the hive, Nyx grants one of her Assassins the Carapace of the Sacred Orb. It is the most painful of molts...but legend requires great sacrifice.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Orb_Helm: The Nyx Assassin, under the influence of the Sacred Orb, perceives even more of Nyx's bounty: So many targets to reap!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Orb_Set: Includes all items in the 'Sacred Orb' set for Nyx Assassin:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Orb_Venom_Claws: Against certain foes, the Nyx assassin imbues its blades with a venom that is their only weakness. Praise Nyx that they have even one such vulnerability!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacrificial_Blade_of_the_: The blade has seen the belly of many a beast so that knowledge may pour forth and forewarn those in need.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacrificial_Shortblade: If it was good enough to cut the heart from a heretic, then it is good enough to cut the heart from anyone.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Salvaged_Sword_and_Board: Sometimes you have to go with what you can find.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Samsung_Dota_2_Pro_League: The Cybergamer Pro League allows professional teams to compete for a prize pool which grows the more teams that participate!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Samurai_Soul: Contains all of the items in the 'Samurai Soul' set for Earthshaker plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sandworn_Visage_of_the_An: Unearthed from the sand-scoured ruins of El'Harath, from this Visage the entire culture of the Sovereign has been resurrected.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sange_and_Yasha: A pair of magical short blades, balanced and light. Unpack this bundle to receive both Sange and Yasha for Riki.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sange_the_Backseeker: Sange, one of the two legendary moonblades, is said to be unnaturally accurate and able to change to a form that best fits the fighting style of its owner. In the hands of Riki the weapon becomes a small dagger.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sanguine_Moon_Armor: An eye for an eye makes leaves all the heroes blind.  Except for Lycan, because he's darn sure not going to lose his second eye.  You can be sure of that.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sanguine_Moon_Belt: Some have questioned the fashion sense of using a skull for a belt buckle.  The last guy who questioned it became a second belt buckle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sanguine_Moon_Head: That's not an eye-patch.  That's armor for his vision.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sanguine_Moon_Shoulder: For some heroes, a shoulder isn't a deadly weapon capable of eviscerating enemies.  Lycan isn't one of those heroes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sanguine_Royalty: Contains all of the items in the 'Sanguine Royalty' set for Queen of Pain plus loading screen. These items were created in partnership with Mushi, who will who receive a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sapphire_Cask: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. The items in this treasure will not be tradable or marketable until March 1st, 2015.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sash_of_Divine_Ascension: A neatly tied sash is all one needs when extracting ascended vengeance.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sash_of_Yoskreth: In his gratitude, the sovereign of Yoskreth bid that fine robes be made for the warrior who had bested Sahsk's vile enchantments.

The falcon seal upon the sash is granted only to distinguished veterans of naval warfare.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scarab_Pendant_of_the_Pri: This is no false idol, but an idol true, from which the sacred scarab of the faith may one day spread its golden wings and fly.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scarf_of_the_Deadly_Night: Whosoever wears this mantle, the spirit Tyrian ensures they shall shrug off any burden, while their identity and their purpose remain concealed.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scepter_of_Corrupted_Ambe: Far away beneath the Sunken Cities and through the Infernal Hollow, Buki'vak the Corrupted dwells in the depths forever expanding his corruption throughout the sea. Hearing of his power, Lion seeked to harvest his parts for a fresh demonoplasty. After a strenuous battle he defeated Buki'vak and gained the hand he desired as a reward, but it was not without cost. Just as his previous hand transformed him, so did this one. He became afflicted with the Malignant Corruption, causing unseemly shards of Obsidian to grow from his body and further disfigure him into something even more unrecognizeable from his original form.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scepter_of_the_Grand_Magu: Few know that Rubick's talents for mimicry extend to arcane assembly.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scepter_of_the_Sable_Void: To harness the powers of the burning nether requires a symbol feared for its malice.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scions_of_the_Sky_Loading: By wing and way, victory will be theirs.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Screeauks_Talon: Scree'auk's Talon was fashioned by a certain winged Mage, forged from shades of unrequited passion, tempered in grief, and quenched in the secret tears of her admirer. More's the pity that she uses it now, approximately half the time, to hunt him.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sculptors_Monument: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. This treasure contains individual items.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sculptors_Pillar: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. This treasure contains individual items.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scuttling_Scotty: Separated from his flock in an ice storm, the adventurous young pengling Scotty wandered the Blueheart Glacier, starving and alone, until he found himself rescued by a certain young Ice Maiden. Crystal Maiden nursed him back to health with love and fishy treats. Swearing to return her kindness, Scotty swore off adventuring, and now he has no urge other than to carry supplies and treats to those in need.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scythe_of_Vyse: The most guarded relic of the cult of Vyse, it is a weapon coveted for its magical properties.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sea_Dragons_Armlet: The scaly hide of the Sea Dragon is one of the few substances tougher than Slardar's own integument.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sea_Dragons_Fins: What appear as fins on Slardar are but the edge of the mighty Sea Dragon's tiniest gill-guards.

Atop the head of the scion's undead champion sat the Searing Dominator, a helm that ignited the blood of its wearer to fuel its terrible power.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shell_of_the_Hidden_Hive: Only those who preside in the Hidden Hive and share in the schemes of the goddess Nyx know the true significance of this ceremonial armor.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shield_of_Burning_Turmoil: Cooled in the black nether between worlds, its core still bends and burns.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shield_of_Endless_Havoc: Let them loose their arrows and fling their axes.  The shield cares not.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shield_of_Stillness: This shield emanates calm and stillness, quieting Silencer's nearby foes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shield_of_the_Drake: Although forged from silver and jeweled with crimsonstone, this enchanted Shield of the Drake is no ornamental bauble to hefted at tourneys.  It is the deepest kind of magic, and its bearer could find no better protection.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shield_of_the_Hidden_Tale: Whatever magic his enemies use, whatever spells his foes may cast in his direction, bounce soundlessly off this shield of silence.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shield_of_the_Silent_Guar: Sometimes a lack of magic is the greatest magic of all.  But for those times when it isn't, this shield might help.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shift_of_the_Silent_Guard: Cloaked in Silence, and also in this stylish shift.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shock_of_the_Anvil: No mere battle hammer this. The Shock of the Anvil is the immovable object upon which a generation of weapons were born. Each battered and shaped upon the iron, and each imparting some vital essence, until at last the anvil crackled with piezoelectric power. When Magnus saw the hammer the blacksmith intended for him, he scoffed, choosing instead to make a weapon of the anvil itself.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shooting_Star: Contains the Shooting Star set for Sniper, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Short_Blade_of_Distant_Sa: Few assassins would dare use with such a finely wrought implement in combat, yet to the skilled this blade offers balance and sharpness more than equal to any task.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulder_of_the_Atniw: Ferocity takes shape.  Huge shoulders rise to shrug off attack.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulder_of_the_Golden_Ma: In each ferocious face is set determination without fear.  Such is required from those who would don the honors of the Golden Mane.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulder_of_the_Noble: Each nobleblood general of the Royal House of Ambry bore these pauldrons as a part of their formal wear.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulderguard_of_the_Free: Rogue swordmasters must balance the need for protection with the need for speed. This pauldron protects Sven's leading shoulder, but leaves his back arm unencumbered.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulderguards_of_the_Pen: The shoulderguards reflect the heavenly light above as a beacon of salvation visible from leagues away.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulderpads_of_the_Falco: Only a diving falcon can hope to avoid Windranger's arrows.  But this one didn't.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_Claszureme: For a traveler from Claszureme, one's place in the flow of time is uncertain.  These runes help ground the wearer within time's march.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Comets_T: The stars themselves travel the skies in search of illumination.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Dark_Mag: In an age when fear surrounded sorcery, tales told of an oppressive wizard capable of limitless destruction.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Death_Ch:
It took the steel of two shields, melted down and recast, to cover the broad shoulders of Spirit Breaker.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Forest_H: Deep in his thoughts, Earthshaker scarcely notices the occasional hop-on.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Fungal_L: Infused with the essence of the Father Mushroom.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Hidden_T: When a heavy silence falls, Nortrom will need mighty shoulders such as these to bear up under its weight.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_North: Keep the snow off your shoulders in these furry shoulders of winter.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Slain_Dr: Not the actual shoulders of a dragon, but a skilled artist's rendition of it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Twelfth_: In the custom of the Bear Clan, each warrior must carry his newborn in a satchel on his shoulder for eleven full days to prove his strength.  On the twelfth day, armor is bestowed.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_ShowMatch_Coliseo: The first season for the ShowMatch Coliseo league hosted by Isurus Gaming and Not Today.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shredder_of_the_Vandal: If you run out of arrows, you can always stab your enemies with this.  It has more points than Leshrac has horns.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shroom_Thing: Constructed from fungus and moss and infused with the essence of the Father Mushroom.. Shroom Thing is here to serve!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shroomling: Among all the shuffling fungi of Drowned Forest, Shroomlings are renowned for their fearless nature and love of all things dank and dark.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shroud_of_Ka: Includes custom abilty icon and custom particle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shroud_of_the_Archivist: Prevents cranial intrusions by a particularly pernicious form of bookwyrm that skulks in the Ultimyr Archives.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shroud_of_the_Awakened: May thine visage not be hindered by those of absent mind and eternal hunger, for thou shall bring an end to their suffering... - Taken from Tael'Am.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shroud_of_the_Shattered_S: To possess the power of a Demon Witch is to stand in defiance of powers seen and unseen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shrunken_Head_Staff: The head of Witch Doctor's mother hangs from this staff. Such a loving son.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shuriken_of_Distant_Sands: Those who worship the Solar Goddess of the eastern wastes are known for the skill forging gold.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shuriken_of_the_Blood_Sta: Flying edges bite, and the sand is christened anew.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shuriken_of_the_Crimson_C: Among the many weapons in the Crimson Cut-throat's home were a trio of small, curved knives which Gondar repurposed into a new shuriken.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shuriken_of_the_Hidden_Hu: This shuriken's blades are clean and sharp, a weapon fresh and ready.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shuriken_of_the_Reaper: A shuriken made to be deadly regardless of how it makes contact.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sigil_Belt_of_the_Great_G: An protective iron belt hammered into the likeness of a wolf.  Long may the last of his house stalk the woods of Ambry.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sigil_of_the_Radiant_Crus: Those who don these fabrics must swear never to fall in battle, for it is considered a sin to defile such a garment with earth.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sigil_of_the_Stormcrow: A staff bearing the sigil of the stormcrow, crafted from its sacred bones.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sigil_of_the_Tahlin_Watch: Very few display the talent necessary to join the Tahlin Watch.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Silent_Champion: Contains all of the items in the 'Silent Champion' set for Silencer:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Silver_Dota_League: A South american league that help the teams to gain points in the rankings of Dota 2 Brazlian teams made by fans!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Silver_Dota_League_2: The Silver Dota League is an Amateur league featuring more than 100 South American teams competing for in-game items and a cash prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Silver_Spectator_Gem: Adding this gem to an item will enable that item to track games viewed for a league or team.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sina_Cup_Seaosn_5: The fifth season of the Sina Cup has Chinese teams competing for a prize pool of 100,000 Yuan!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sina_Cup_Supernova_Dota_2: The Sina Cup Supernova Dota 2 puts two top teams from the qualifiers against professional teams across Asia for a total prize pool of 30,000RMB.
Sina Cup Supernova Dota 2 Open is back for another season! In addition to the 8 invited teams, 4 teams will advance through qualifiers to compete for a total prize pool of 65,000RMB.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sina_Cup_Supernova_Season: Supernova tradition continues on with rising teams qualifying for chance to compete against top teams across China for prize pool of 90,000RMB.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Single_Battle_Point_Boost:
Use this item to increase the rate at which you earn Battle Points to 150% for a single match. Additionally, you will grant other players a stacking 5% bonus to their Battle Points rate.

Battle Point Boosters are only consumed whenever Battle Points are earned and features like spectating games or coaching do not deplete them.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Single_Item_Treasure: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. This treasure contains individual items.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sinister_Lightning: Includes all of the items in the 'Sinister Lightning' set for Invoker including alternate styles and a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sinorian_Sphere_Staff: A Sinorian gemstone caps this staff, providing a magical focus for nature's incantations.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sithils_Stash: That disreputable scoundrel Sithil has lost a chest of plundered loot! You will need <font color='#9da1a9'>Sithil's Summer Key</font> to open the chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Beware! At the end of <font color='#9da1a9'>July 31, 2012</font> this chest will crumble into useless dust. This chest contains one of several mysterious new items.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sizzling_Charge: Contains the Sizzling Charge set for Storm, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skeletal_Catch: There might still be a little meat on it.  But probably not.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skeletal_Claw_of_the_Vand: Lacking flesh, Clinkz adorns his skeletal hand with the claw of the Vandal.  Forged by smeevils in ages long past, this iron claw is for many hapless victims the iron grip of death itself.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skins_of_the_Incubus: Few facets of the utter foul wander the land unbidden. To claim such a skin is to declare primacy over the inferno.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skip_the_Delivery_Frog: What he lacks in size he makes up for in character.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skirt_of_the_Flameguard: Beyond reproach and unwavering in their devotion, the Flameguard stand as living avatars of Knightly Duty.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skirt_of_the_Mage_Slayer: Time and practice would persuade the Anti-Mage against such a heavy garment, yet its use in combat has not diminished.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skirt_of_the_Revenant: A new storm is blowing across the battlefield.  Where there is thunder, there is sure to be lighting.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skittering_Desolation: When Weaver slipped through time, he found something impossible just beyond the rift.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skull_Mask_o_Wicked_Badne: A mask crafted from the polished bones of a cruel Prefecturan noble. The Witch Doctor wears this mask when he wants influential spirits to take notice of his work.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skull_Staff_of_Grim_Rites: The life essence of a sacrificial totem beast imbues this ritual staff.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skull_of_the_Ravager: Only the fiercest hunter may lay claim to the skull of a spiked ravager.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skullsplitter_Axe: Axe never had the heart to wipe the original owner's blood from the edge.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_SkyHigh_Warship: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Sky-High Warship' set for Gyrocopter plus loading screen. These items were created in partnership with Alliance, who receive a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skywarriors_Countenance: A holy relic passed down from the emperors of the ancient clouded city of Aesthera, this spellbound helm bestows the golden visage of the vulture goddess upon only the most elite warriors of the realm.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skywrath_Sentinel: Although she may never reach the lofty hights of the Ghastly Eyrie again, Shendelzare still has allies that will grant her assistance when she requires it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slarks_Hood: This new item has no description.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slashing_Quickslicer: If cross words lead to crossed swords, then it's best to be polite to the Naga Siren.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slashing_Quickslicer_Pack: This bundle contains both the main and off-hand Slashing Quickslicer.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slashing_Quickslicer__Off: If cross words lead to crossed swords, then it's best to be polite to the Naga Siren.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_SlayerSword_of_Sir_Davion: When facing a dragon the edge of one's blade means less than the sharpness of one's mind.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slayers_Glare: Why light a fire if you can't watch it burn?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sleeves_of_the_Charred_Bl: The rubies sewn into the sleeves are prized among the Misrule nobility.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sleeves_of_the_Ephemeral_: A billowing sleeve for Spectre, charged with the excess energy that overflows from Spectre's present form.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sleeves_of_the_Scorching_: The sleeves flare out like the fiery soul who wears them.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sleeves_of_the_Solar_Divi: During her training in the flame arts, Lina chose to travel east to study with the followers of the Solar Goddess.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slicer_of_the_Depths: A shiv assembled from contraband gems. Better not ask how Slark kept it concealed in Dark Reef Prison.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slim_Blade_of_the_Tahlin_: When death is the price, one can never swing too many blades.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Smeevil: Tis said among artisan and warrior alike that there is no finer servant than a trusty smeevil.  However, a hero who chooses a smeevil as their courier may soon find these clever critters taking new forms in order to gain assistants of their own. Inspired by the great battles they bear witness to, a smeevil may become emboldened to press ever more exotic beasts to their cause.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Smeevil_Treat: A tasty snack used to unlock new Smeevil styles.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Smoke_Bomb_of_Wild_Repris: Includes particles and an ability icon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Smoldering_Journey: Includes all of the items in the 'Smoldering Journey' set for Lina plus a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snaggletooth: From the forests beneath the Wailing Mountains, a new friend and companion appears, small in stature but enormous in spirit.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snelfret_the_Snail: The original rebel snail, Snelfret refused to conform to a social order that enforced lethargy, a world that told him he must not move too fast. So he loaded up his shell and headed for more dynamic climes, determined to redefine the meaning of snail's pace.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_SngLadder_Season_One: Hundreds of players fight for the top spot and valuable prizes in the SngLadder Season One League.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snowdrop_Hood: Able to withstand the toughest onslaughts with nary a hair out of place, the Maiden of the North gives truth to the old adage that looks can kill.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snowdrop_Mantle: For those times when giving someone the cold shoulder is only the beginning.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snowdrop_Mittens: Crystal Maiden hardly needs to keep her hands warm in freezing weather. We suspect these are strictly a fashion statement.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snowdrop_Staff: Not one for outward displays of force, Crystal Maiden understands the necessity of putting on a show. This brilliant staff is but a symbol of her inner power, and for all its luster, barely hints at the depths of her mastery.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snowdrop_Tassels: No Wolf of Icewrack tail was harmed in the making of these tassels. They are formed entirely of soft, fluffy ice.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snowl: The Goddess of the Moon presses many forest creatures into her service.  Always crafty, ever vigilant, little Snowl would give his all to aid the guardians of the Nightsilver.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snowstorm_Huntress: Contains all of the items in the 'Snowstorm Huntress' item set for Mirana plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Solo_Mid_Battle_by_Terrik: Players from CIS will fight for the RAR.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sorcerer_of_the_Black_Poo: Includes all of the items in the 'Dead Winter' set for Lich plus a loading screen:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Soul_Diffuser: By this blade shall you know her, bringer of death, bearer of your final moments of mortal terror.  She who renders your soul diffuse, your body lifeless dark, mere meat and viscera.  In a flash of movement, she slices your soul's tether, and frees you to learn the truth of the last great mystery.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Soulhook_Bracer: Lich could not help but notice the efficiency of hooks deployed by certain other heroes. Nor has his enthusiasm for learning new tricks cooled.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_South_American_Amateur_Do: Where all amateurs South American Teams fight for Glory and a prize in cash!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_South_American_Elite_Leag: The most talented players in South America compete for $1,000 in the classic in-house league format for six weeks.
The most talented players in South America compete in the classic inhouse league format.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_South_American_Fire_Cup: The best cup with the best South American amateur teams compete for a $320 prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_South_Sumatera_DOTA_2_Ama: The second annual DOTA 2 competition for all amateur team in South Sumatera region sponsored by Command Centre Game Station and Intikom.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_South_Sumatera_Dota_2_Ama: South Sumatera Dota 2 Amateur League is a Dota 2 competition between 15 most talented amateur teams in the region.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_South_Ural_League_Season_: Teams compete in an online competition to earn a spot in the top 16 teams which compete in a LAN finals.

The third season of the South Ural League is upon us! The league consists of 16 teams in the pro division and 80 teams in the amateur division. The LAN finals will take place in Chelyabinsk.  Bundle includes the ticket and Green Ural HUD skin!

The third season of the South Ural League is upon us! The league consists of 16 teams in the pro division and 80 teams in the amateur division. The LAN finals will take place in Chelyabinsk.  This ticket only gives you access to view games from the South Ural League Season 3.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Souvinir_of_the_Bone_Ru: Even skulls get lonely up in the ruins.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sovereign_of_the_Hive: Includes all of the items in the 'Sovereign of the Hive' set for Nyx Assassin plus a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spade_of_the_Gluttonous: Though crafted in symbolic likeness to the great wheel books of the ruined city, the Spade of the Gluttonous whistles no song but the song of death.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Span_of_Black_Nihility: Beneath the wings of Black Nihility lies terrible darkness. Those in their shadow must supplicate and despair.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spanish_Dota_2_Pro_Series: The Spanish Dota 2 Pro Series is the first  professional league for Dota 2 in Spain created with the 8 best teams from Spain!
The finals of the Dota 2 Pro Series are the biggest event of Dota 2 in Spain. The live event will take place in Madrid from June 27th-29th.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sparrowhawk_Bow: Strong, but light as a feather, this bow of the sparrowhawk will fly your arrows true to their targets.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sparrowhawk_Cape: In addition to being stylish, this cape of the sparrowhawk manages the trick of also being camouflaging, provided that you're standing next to a flock of sparrowhawks.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sparrowhawk_Hood: It takes a spectacular hood to tame your fiery red hair.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sparrowhawk_Quiver: Proving that every part of the sparrowhawk can be turned into a stylish item for Lyralei to wear, this quiver speaks to the utility of sparrowhawks as a species.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sparrowhawk_Wings: Tired of your shoulders being devoid of sparrowhawk feathers?  Then this item is for you.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spaulder_of_Burning_Turmo: Within the astral turmoil, heat bends and matter swirls.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spaulder_of_the_Steppe: Many a centaur was gored with this spiny spaulder.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spaulders_of_The_Howling_: Bone-carved shoulder spaulders display the ceremonial markings of the Frosted Winds tribe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spear_of_Teardrop_Ice: The two teardrop gems pressed into the haft ensure the spear's icy edge never thaws.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spear_of_the_Golden_Mane: To wield such a prized spear, one must have courage and ferocity befitting the honors of the Golden Mane.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spear_of_the_Herald: An ancient weapon from an unknown craftsman, it was said to have been forged for he whom destiny calls worthy. Each swing heralds another step toward a new age.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spear_of_the_Wildwings_Bl: It is unfortunate that a few rogue Wildkin must spoil the proud race's reputation, but when it is time to hunt those few rascals down, Enchantress bears a spear granted her by the wisest of the Wildwing race.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spectator_Gem: Adding this gem to an item will enable that item to track games viewed for a league or team.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spectral_Conservator: In her myriad manifestations, Spectre finds herself adapting to the exigencies of war. Slowly, she has converged on a more suitable form.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spectral_Light: When moving between certain dark angles of creation, it is important that one not be mistaken for prey. The sigils on this headpiece serve as a warning to some interdimensional predator, but an invitation to others less visible.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spectrolite_Staff: A staff bearing an array of spectrolite mana focusing crystals set in gold.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Speed_Demon: This imp has trained all his life for this moment. He is SO ready to go. He will deliver your loot on time or suffer eternal damnation in the sixty-four planes of the Lesser Hells.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spell_Surveyor: The Spell Surveyor is always on the lookout for spells that might be stolen!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spellbinders_Catalytic_Ma: When Rubick dons his catalytic mantle, things really start happening.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spellbinders_Forgotten_Gr: Rubick completely forgot about this greatstaff until just this moment!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spellbinders_Mask_of_Shap: Feeling ferocious, or simply for a lark, Rubick likes to take this old thing out and show it off from time to time.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spellbinders_Tattered_Clo: It is difficult in battle for even a great mage to entirely avoid treading on his cloak. Eventually it begins to show wear.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spellbreaker_of_Yoskreth: The sovereign of Yoskreth insisted that their champion be given the finest guard they could forge.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spetum_of_the_Disciplined: While a sharp point may make a weapon dangerous, it takes a disciplined arm to make it deadly.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spider_of_Purple_Nightmar: Includes all of the items in the 'Spider of Purple Nightmare' set for Witch Doctor:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spiked_Bracers_of_the_Rav: To kill a ravager is a sacred rite for the ursa, and every piece of the carcass must be put to use.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spiked_Guard_of_the_Ancie: All who dared stand against the Bramble Lord well knew how easily his powers could catch and pierce their lives.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spiked_Pauldrons_of_the_C: Made from the leather of a full grown thunderhide, this armor is a match for any blade.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spinal_Slicer: The prized spine of a red drake provides this heavy blade with an excellent counter-balance.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spinal_Slicer__OffHand: The prized spine of a red drake provides this heavy blade with an excellent counter-balance.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spinal_Slicers__Pair: Pack includes both the main and off-hand Spinal Slicer.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spine_Sword: Most see being stabbed in the back as a hindrance, but for a few, it's an inspiration.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spine_of_Omexe: Forged from the melted shields of a dozen fallen gladiators, this armor has the centaur's back.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spines_of_the_Dreadful_Ab: From strange waters come stranger properties.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spiral_Staff: A crystalline focus hung at the center of the staff gives the Witch Doctor unnatural sight.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spiral_Staff_of_the_First: A twisted staff that holds a captive memory of the initial blaze of creation.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spirit_Breakers_Head: This new item has no description.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spirit_Crusher: Your enemy's spirits will be crushed by the sight of this dread weapon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spirit_of_Calm: Though doom and ruin they saw, the visions of the haruspex brought to Sylla a sense of destined calm. During mediations, he found his spiritual projections altered to appear less intimidating.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spirit_of_the_Atniw: A projection of inner strength, and the bond of the bear clan.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spirit_of_the_Howling_Wol: Includes all of the items in 'Spirit of The Howling Wolf' set for Sniper:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Splattering_Forcipule: The darkest wilds of Jidi Isle are home to wondrous horrors. A distant relative to the Spitterpede family, the Splattering Forcipule can often be found growing in damp crevices or between the roots of trees. They will spend their entire lives bound to a single location, and the toxic venom they eject upon any creature foolish enough wander nearby is often more than sufficient to poison the hapless victim, as well as begin its digestion. Once this poor soul expires, their melting remains are quickly absorbed into the earth where they fall, allowing the Forcipule's subterranean root-tendrils to absorb the nutrients.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Splintering_Awe: Contains the Splintering Awe set for Treant, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spoils_from_the_Shifting_:
Shatter their sorcery.

These items were created in partnership with BurNing, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spoils_of_the_Bone_Ruins_: Contains all of the items in the 'Spoils of the Bone Ruins' for Meepo:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spottin_Goggles: Able to see a tic on a mouse's back at a thousand paces, Sniper's Spottin' Goggles are a marvel to behold.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Springs_Lilium_Crown: For creatures of the forest, a crown of flowers is more precious than any jewels.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Squiddles: A rather oversized, stuffed squid plushie. He's cute and slimy and his name is Squiddles.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sri_Lanka_Cyber_Games_201: SLCG has become the largest e-Sports tournament in the country, and this year it aims to take the culture of games to the next level. Watch top Dota 2 teams compete in the largest event in Sri Lanka!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sri_Lanka_Cyber_Games_SLC: SLCG has become the largest e-Sports tournament in the country, and this year it aims to take the culture of games to the next level. Watch top Dota 2 teams compete in the largest event in Sri Lanka!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Staff_of_Divine_Ascension: A staff so powerful it can grant the bearer powers from a plane beyond ascension.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Staff_of_Infernal_Chaos: A Dreadwood staff  engraved with hellish runes to confine a spirit from the Outer Hells inside it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Staff_of_Inscrutable_Zeal: The coil along the staff allows the caster to embellish the course of whatever energies it may release.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Staff_of_Retribution: Skywrath Mage carries a special staff for every occasion. This one marks an occasion of retribution.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Staff_of_Wind_and_Sand: As wind and sand can wear down a mountain, so too this magical staff can wear down even the greatest foe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Staff_of_the_Archivist: The measured thud of this staff may be heard in the labyrinthine corridors of the Ultimyr Archives as often as these ominous words: Now where did I put that book?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Staff_of_the_Cruel_Magici:
Through the darkest channels travel the most powerful sorceries.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Staff_of_the_Crystalline_: Locked frozen in a glacier for a thousand years, this great staff was carved long ago in honor of the twin northern stars.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Staff_of_the_Eagle: The prophet of Nature is not only a ward of the green things, but also of the myriad beasts and birds.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Staff_of_the_Frozen_Feath: A day before the wizard descended into the glacier to begin his hibernation, he offered Crystal Maiden these last, precious gifts: armor and a staff, strong as ice but light as a feather, believed to have once belonged to a winter deity.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Staff_of_the_Fungal_Lord: Infused with the essence of the Father Mushroom.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Staff_of_the_Glacier_Dust:
Imbued with the essence of ancient glaciers, its icy prow is as light as a feather.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Staff_of_the_Northlight: Ezalor is known throughout the realms as Keeper of the radiance of day, but legends from the remote, snowbound villages of the Wailing Mountains tell of him appearing in another guise: that of a champion of the lost, a bearer of the guiding light of the North Star.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Staff_of_the_Old_Doctor: When the Witch Doctor rose to his position of power over his tribe, he fashioned this staff from the remains of the old Doctor. Perhaps it was meant as an honor, but most saw it as a warning.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Stag_of_the_Northlight: The Keeper is said to travel the icy Northern wastes astride a magnificent stag, giving aid to those in greatest need and vanquishing evil and darkness wherever it is found.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Staglift: The Mk. 44 0-590 Staglift Courierdrone represents the latest in donkey technology. Built with steel composite ablative plating to protect an air-sealed pocket containing the actual donkey brain which controls its motor functions, heroes can rest assured that the Staglift will not stop, ever, until its items are delivered.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Stalwart_Sentinel: The heft and shape of the blade spells danger for both the target and the wielder.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Stanley_Parable_Announcer: This pack replaces the Default announcer and Mega-Kills announcer with the sardonically meta wit of the Narrator from The Stanley Parable.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sufferwood_Sapling: Nature is not a unified cause or philosophy. Feared by all that is green, the tainted Sufferwood hosts a consciousness bent on dominating everything that grows, sending forth blooming horrors to corrupt the wilds to its purpose.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Summers_Mirth: Mirth and merriment bedeck the lovely Enchantress. Ivy is cool in summer and who cares about winter anyway?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Summers_Warmth: Every warm summer day must eventually give way to the cool breezes of evening. This light covering is more than enough to ward off goosebumps.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sweaty_Cup_2_Ticket: 32 semi-pro and professional teams participate in the 2nd season of the Sweaty Tournament with a $1,200 prize pool. This ticket only gives access to view games from the Sweaty Cup 2 Tournament.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sweep_of_Black_Nihility: The presence of primordial night lingers even as darkness passes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sweep_of_Forsaken_Beauty: Silken cloths sweep the ground where Medusa wanders.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Swift_Claw: You may flee from his rage. You may leave his echoing roar far behind. And you may think yourself safe, perhaps in a clearing or canyon, with no sign of your pursuer. Then, suddenly, his claws find you, and it is the last you know.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Swine_Arsenal: Techies Demolitions built hundreds of custom-built explosives to use with The Swine, but Spleen thought they were so adorable he couldn't bear to part with them as they were loading the cannon onboard the galley.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Swine_Helmet: When constructing The Swine, Techies Demolitions also forged some stylish headgear for its crew.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Swine_Powder_Barrel: Safely firing The Swine requires a custom mix of flammable powders, which Squee completely forgot to mention to the crew of the doomed galley who purchased the cannon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Swine_Visor: For some reason, the galley captain who commissioned The Swine didn't want the headgear that came with it. His loss.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_Impending_Transg: A sword ever being forged, red hot, glowing with the heat of all the seven hells.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_the_Admirable_Ad: An exceptional specimen, surely the Captain's first pick of the loot. The hilt is dressed in worked gold and exotic stones. The blade blessed with a strangely glowing enchantment.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_the_Drake: One of only a dozen swords in existence known to have slain more than one dragon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_the_Flameguard: A heavily weighted sword fashioned in the two-handed style of the Flameguard sect of the Vigil Knights.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_the_Freelancer: Bitter the orphans journey--and lonely the orphan's grave.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_the_Mono_Militis: The Mono Militis are one of several sects among the Vigil Knights. Adherents have tasked themselves with hunting down those who have strayed from the teachings of the Vigil Codex.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_the_Seventy_Seve: Here we have a weapon truly worthy of a man such as Kunkka. Exotic and well-balanced, this cutlass cuts an image as smartly as it cuts a man.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_the_Warriors_Ret: A weapon that once belonged to Sven's father, it was years before the son discovered its transformative properties.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylnashar_the_Winged_Axe: Lost for centuries, the winged axe known as Sylnashar was once the favored weapon of an ancient king.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Cascade: A cape woven from the finest wind-strewn filaments of enchanted ephemera, this is a garment of both rare beauty and unexpected utility.  For she who wears the cape of the Sylvan Cascade, the wind will be always at her back.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Guards_Boots: The guardians of the forest paths walk in perfect silence, betrayed not by their cunning footwear.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Guards_Bow: Drow has nothing to learn from the Sylvan Guard, but from time to time she relieves one of them of their bow, that she might test its quality. Even by her standards, this one is adjudged very fine.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Guards_Cape: Stealth is of utmost importance to those who number themselves among the Sylvan Guard. Even Drow finds this an acceptable cape for moving unseen through the wooded ways.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Guards_Cuffs: In her youth, Drow was tempted once or twice to throw over her lonely ways and join the Sylvan Guard. These cuffs were a large part of the attraction.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Guards_Dress_Armor: It must be admitted: Drow admires the Sylvan Guard. When from time to time she puts on their gear, and pretends to adopt their ways, she can hardly suppress her joy in having an excuse to don this stylish armor.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Guards_Finery_Set: All the finery of the Sylvan Guard, complete!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Guards_Hair: While not a member of the Sylvan Guard, Drow spies upon them in their marches, and occasionally admires their passing fashions.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Guards_Quiver: The archers of the Sylvan Guard shoot only arrows crafted specifically for their use. When Drow uses their gear, such arrows are de rigeur.

This bundle includes the Warhawk Vestiments Lina set andy grants access to view games from the Synergy League Season 1.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Synergy_League_Season_1_T: The top teams from Europe, South-East Asia, and China compete for the $50,000+ prize pool. This ticket only grants access to view games from the Synergy League Season 1.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Team_Dignitas: Show your support for a team by buying this Team Pennant! Equip it in the 'fan slot' of your Player Loadout to show other spectators who you're rooting for. Pennants can be combined with other pennants to upgrade your Team Pennant fan level.  The level of your Team Pennant will increase the total fan value of the team when you are spectating a Tournament match.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Techies_Arcana: After months of work, Techies Demolitions proudly unveiled their latest commission: The Swine, the most powerful cannon ever designed. Yet during its first frantic use aboard a homebound galley, the Swine's awesome blast tore its host ship asunder, rocketing the cannon itself backwards toward the shore. It was found days later, deeply embedded in a rocky cliffside just below its makers' workshop.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Techlabs_Cup_Grand_Final: Techlabs Cup Grand Final in Moscow on November 16-17 where teams compete for a total prize pool of $25,000!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Techlabs_Moscow_Cup_2014: The Techlabs Cup returns with a prize pool of $20,000 up for grabs. Featuring both established and upcoming teams, the tournament will showcase what the CIS region has to offer. Bundle includes the official Techlabs Moscow Cup 2014 HUD skin!

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Techno_Int_DX_Dota_2_Tour: The second series of DX Indonesia Dota 2 Tournament. This tournament consist of 96 teams from Indonesia competing for a $2,000 prize pool. This tournament is proudly sponsored by Intel Indonesia.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Teeth_of_the_Eternal_Ligh: Forged in a realm best left forgotten, these teeth induce agony from nerves that reach beyond mortal experience.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Telebolt_Projektor: Some inventions are too controversial for their age. When the Telebolt Projektor was first unveiled almost a century ago, the audience quickly decided that the thunderous energy of heavens should probably stay in the heavens.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Barb_of_Skadi: Deep in Dark Reef Prison, a sorcerer and a blacksmith combined their trades to create a unique weapon. Fashioned from found materials,  the blade can open prison walls as easily as it opens bellies.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Barren_Crown: Heavy is the head that wears the crown, and never has this been more true than with Sand King, who wears the crest of the Barrens upon his head. A Crown of ancient provenance, forged of magic and gemstones by the Spire Mage, it transforms the wearer for all time into the ruler of desert wanderers and sovereign of the Barren lands.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Basher_Blades: The fabled blades that shattered the Anvil Magus Hroth. Its terrible weight dented and shattered his iron shell, just as its blades tore into the enchanted hide beneath.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Brood_Queen_Set: Many are the knights and noble youths who have intruded on the hunting grounds of the Broodmother, disturbing her peace with the clatter of armor, their boots setting atwitch her silken web. The intruders are like succulent shelled insects upon whose innards she's gorged, all the while growing curious of the adornments that drape their bodies, until that day when a blacksmith found his way into her web.  Armor he promised her, the finest in the land, if only she would set him free. And so a deal was struck, and the blacksmith measured, and toiled, taking as his materials the finest steel to be found among the husked corpses of silk-wrapped knights.  When the new armor was finished, the spider kept her promise and set the blacksmith free.  Then she watched her brood devour him. Contains all of the items in the 'Brood Queen' set for Broodmother:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Burden_of_Eleven_Curs: He that burns and is not consumed now walks the battlefield, shielded by the ancient promise of the Eleven Curses. Eleven Eyes, eleven seals, eleven curses. All to insure victory in even the worst of battles. Contains all of the items in 'The Burden of Eleven Curses' set for Doom Bringer:

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Children_of_Verodicia: Amongst the first born of the forest, these spry treants have been with the Prophet since time immemorial.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Commendable_Commodore: Kunkka lives by the old seaman's yarn: There is no bad weather, only poor clothes.  In this regal finery, Kunkka is ready to face any storm.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Commodores_Bicorne: Rain, nor waves, nor driving wind can chill Kunkka's head while he's wearing this noble cowl.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Commodores_Curtains: Many a storm has sluiced down upon these broad shoulders, now protected from the stormy seas by this stylish all-weather gear.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Commodores_Facings: Woven from the finest, tight-knitted fabrics, this heavy chest-piece protects from both the elements and errant blades.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Gallows_Understudy_Se:
Far from the temples of the Flayed Twins, Bloodseeker stumbled upon a land that lauded execution above sacrifice, relying on hempen rope and metal blades instead of black stone and the will of bloodthirsty gods. Yet there was something in their crude approach that appealed to him, and so he spent a season studying the executioners, watching from the crowd that turned out for every morbid spectacle, until he realized that the mob itself was the god to whom they made their sacrifices. With a leer that matched those to be seen on the faces of the enrapt audience, he made his way home to share the lessons he had learned with his own bloody masters of the priestly caste. 
	
	Includes all items from the Gallows Understudy Set.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Gallows_Understudy_Sk: Bloodseeker found many uses for the gallows rope he stole from a corpse's distended neck, in order to study this crude means of execution at his leisure.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Mysterious_Vagabond_S: In the final years of the Sordid Era, after thirteen seasons of drought, shamanic ways fell into disrepute, with all itinerant mages blamed for failing crops and disease. In order to continue his travels, Rhasta was forced to adopt a new appearance. While still offering many of the same services, during the end of this Era he disclaimed all knowledge of shamanism and professed only the knowledge that any vagabond might acquire along the road, and practice (in a strictly nonprofessional sense) for a few coins. Thus he survived into the next era, when many another was separated from their hide and stretched out along the roads as a warning to the next shaman who might happen along. Contains all of the items in the 'Mysterious Vagabond' set for Shadow Shaman:

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Riftshadow_Roamers_Se: Trinkets and tall tales are just a few of the ways a drifter can make a living out in Riftshadow, but there's a lot more in the waste if you know how to look, and where. You'll want a guide and someone who knows their way in a fight, that should let you scratch the surface and take in some history. Getting rich from the ruins though, that's another matter. If you want to learn Riftshadow's darkest secrets, you better tip well and know how to keep your mouth shut. This here bundle includes all of the items in 'The Riftshadow Roamer' set for Meepo:
